1
00:01:52,294 --> 00:01:53,495
Just one episode in,

2
00:01:53,496 --> 00:01:56,598
and this show has already taken me
on an emotional roller coaster.

3
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:58,032
This is way too spicy!

4
00:01:58,033 --> 00:01:58,733
(Jang Woo Young)

5
00:01:58,734 --> 00:02:01,102
Personally, I can't stop thinking
about Jun Han.

6
00:02:01,404 --> 00:02:03,872
- I feel bad for him.
- What's he going to do now?

7
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:06,842
I never expected
Yun So to be this popular.

8
00:02:07,243 --> 00:02:08,944
And when it comes to Jin Woo...

9
00:02:09,178 --> 00:02:11,412
I still can't tell who he likes.

10
00:02:12,015 --> 00:02:14,216
After receiving no votes
in the First Impression Vote,

11
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:16,852
he used his special benefit on Ju Hee.

12
00:02:16,853 --> 00:02:19,388
- The two of them talked for 30 minutes.
- Right.

13
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:22,558
And after getting under Yun So's skin
like that,

14
00:02:23,026 --> 00:02:25,794
he sent his Love QR to Ji Hye.

15
00:02:25,795 --> 00:02:28,297
The First Impression Vote
and the Love QR...

16
00:02:28,831 --> 00:02:30,198
completely changed everything.

17
00:02:30,199 --> 00:02:32,333
Still, I think we need
to watch a little longer.

18
00:02:32,334 --> 00:02:33,335
It's still only the first day.

19
00:02:33,336 --> 00:02:34,402
I'm so curious.

20
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:39,041
(After the first Love QR...)

21
00:02:39,042 --> 00:02:42,778
(Yeon House)

22
00:02:43,946 --> 00:02:45,513
(The Love Benefit is awarded to Ji Hye.)

23
00:02:45,514 --> 00:02:49,617
Ji Hye went from 0 votes to 2.

24
00:02:49,618 --> 00:02:51,186
- That's unexpected too.
- I know.

25
00:02:53,456 --> 00:02:56,858
Can you find out someone's age
in the Secret Room?

26
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:59,361
You can get a clue
that helps you figure it out.

27
00:02:59,362 --> 00:03:00,562
("Open the drawer and guess their age.")

28
00:03:01,397 --> 00:03:03,398
This is important.
It's her first time in the Secret Room.

29
00:03:03,399 --> 00:03:04,566
(She enters for the first time.)

30
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:08,403
(Which younger man is
she most curious about?)

31
00:03:09,238 --> 00:03:10,038
(Is it Jun Han?)

32
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:12,007
- It was Jun Han for her First Impression.
- I know.

33
00:03:12,742 --> 00:03:15,277
But she sent her Love QR to Yun So.

34
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:16,311
(Or is it Yun So?)

35
00:03:16,913 --> 00:03:18,747
(Whose age does she want
to know the most?)

36
00:03:18,748 --> 00:03:20,849
- I think she'll choose Yun So.
- This is a crucial moment.

37
00:03:21,417 --> 00:03:22,784
- Who is it?
- Which one?

38
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:30,125
(After some thought,
Ji Hye opens a drawer.)

39
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:31,593
(Lee Yun So)

40
00:03:31,594 --> 00:03:32,494
(Ji Hye chooses Yun So.)

41
00:03:32,495 --> 00:03:33,962
- It's Yun So!
- Yun So.

42
00:03:34,664 --> 00:03:36,064
- What's that?
- A photo.

43
00:03:37,433 --> 00:03:38,466
(Laughing)

44
00:03:39,228 --> 00:03:41,029
I opened Yun So's.

45
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:47,342
(She studies the photo carefully.)

46
00:03:47,744 --> 00:03:50,379
He looked like he was
in his twenties there.

47
00:03:51,948 --> 00:03:53,148
Maybe mid-twenties?

48
00:03:54,617 --> 00:03:56,551
Twenty-seven...

49
00:03:57,153 --> 00:03:58,520
or twenty-eight at most?

50
00:03:58,755 --> 00:03:59,888
That's barely any information.

51
00:04:00,857 --> 00:04:04,626
The photo was taken in 2021.

52
00:04:04,627 --> 00:04:05,828
In 2021?

53
00:04:06,195 --> 00:04:07,428
That was five years ago.

54
00:04:08,297 --> 00:04:12,200
Looking at this picture,
he could have been in his early twenties.

55
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:14,636
He actually looks younger now.

56
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:16,404
I'm even more confused.

57
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,373
I don't think he's in his early twenties.

58
00:04:19,374 --> 00:04:21,409
Usually, people bleach their hair...

59
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:23,879
and take photos like that
right after turning twenty.

60
00:04:24,213 --> 00:04:25,947
- No, I'm sure he's not.
- He's not in his early twenties.

61
00:04:25,948 --> 00:04:27,349
He feels more like mid-twenties.

62
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,517
Definitely mid-twenties or older.

63
00:04:30,219 --> 00:04:31,553
(Staring)

64
00:04:34,724 --> 00:04:39,328
(How old is Yun So really?)

65
00:04:41,798 --> 00:04:45,734
(Yun So, another recipient
of the most Love QRs,)

66
00:04:45,735 --> 00:04:49,371
(enters the room.)

67
00:04:50,206 --> 00:04:53,742
Last week, he received Love QRs
from Yu Jin, Ji Hye, and Ju Hee.

68
00:04:53,743 --> 00:04:56,745
Three older women chose Yun So.

69
00:04:57,847 --> 00:04:59,548
Ever since the first day,

70
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,850
Yun So has shown interest in Ju Hee.

71
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:03,551
Now he might start wavering.

72
00:05:03,786 --> 00:05:04,853
- Will he?
- Of course.

73
00:05:04,854 --> 00:05:06,254
Because three women chose him?

74
00:05:06,255 --> 00:05:07,088
Sure.

75
00:05:07,089 --> 00:05:07,989
Maybe he will.

76
00:05:07,990 --> 00:05:09,224
(Convinced)

77
00:05:10,259 --> 00:05:14,496
(Will he stick to his first impression,
or will his heart change?)

78
00:05:15,164 --> 00:05:20,201
(Which older woman is
Yun So curious about?)

79
00:05:21,938 --> 00:05:23,805
- If he chooses Ju Hee...
- There he goes.

80
00:05:23,806 --> 00:05:25,708
- That must mean something serious.
- No.

81
00:05:25,709 --> 00:05:26,842
He'll choose someone else.

82
00:05:29,378 --> 00:05:31,613
(The woman in the photo is...)

83
00:05:31,614 --> 00:05:33,681
That photo looks really old!

84
00:05:34,217 --> 00:05:35,783
It looks ancient!

85
00:05:36,018 --> 00:05:37,418
It's not that old!

86
00:05:38,387 --> 00:05:42,156
(The woman in the photo is...)

87
00:05:42,157 --> 00:05:43,057
(Ju Hee)

88
00:05:43,058 --> 00:05:45,126
- It's Ju Hee.
- Oh, it's Ju Hee.

89
00:05:46,329 --> 00:05:47,763
(Tilting his head)

90
00:05:48,665 --> 00:05:49,898
What year was this taken?

91
00:05:52,568 --> 00:05:53,568
"2006?"

92
00:05:54,337 --> 00:05:55,937
Yun So looks completely thrown off.

93
00:05:56,072 --> 00:05:58,407
(The photo says...)

94
00:05:58,408 --> 00:06:00,809
(the year 2006.)

95
00:06:01,911 --> 00:06:03,445
So in 2006...

96
00:06:05,314 --> 00:06:06,247
She was already that grown up?

97
00:06:08,417 --> 00:06:10,218
The photo said 2006.

98
00:06:11,087 --> 00:06:14,189
She looked like a middle school
or a high school student.

99
00:06:14,657 --> 00:06:16,591
I don't think she was in high school.

100
00:06:16,792 --> 00:06:18,292
That hairstyle...

101
00:06:18,794 --> 00:06:21,930
Back in 2006, internet ulzzangs
were everywhere.

102
00:06:21,931 --> 00:06:22,964
- Right.
- Exactly.

103
00:06:22,965 --> 00:06:24,966
Remember Ban Yoon Hee?

104
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,202
- That hairstyle reminds me of her.
- Right.

105
00:06:27,203 --> 00:06:30,105
That means she might be around my age.

106
00:06:30,106 --> 00:06:32,441
It looks exactly like the photos I took
on school trips.

107
00:06:32,775 --> 00:06:34,276
The texture and everything.

108
00:06:34,277 --> 00:06:37,612
Hairstyles always reveal
the era, don't they?

109
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:41,350
- Compared to my birth year...
- And?

110
00:06:41,351 --> 00:06:44,686
I came to the conclusion
that she might be...

111
00:06:44,687 --> 00:06:46,755
much older than I expected.

112
00:06:48,057 --> 00:06:50,091
(Ju Hee in 2006)

113
00:06:50,092 --> 00:06:52,727
(Yun So in 2021)

114
00:06:52,728 --> 00:06:53,928
(How big is the age gap?)

115
00:06:53,929 --> 00:06:56,131
- This is so difficult.
- That's a huge gap.

116
00:06:58,434 --> 00:06:59,734
In 2006...

117
00:07:00,436 --> 00:07:02,737
(Thinking)

118
00:07:03,273 --> 00:07:05,307
I really can't wait for the age reveal.

119
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,342
I'm dying to know.

120
00:07:07,843 --> 00:07:09,510
What if she's twelve years older?

121
00:07:10,112 --> 00:07:12,380
- If that's true...
- That would be shocking.

122
00:07:12,548 --> 00:07:13,615
I'd be completely stunned.

123
00:07:13,849 --> 00:07:15,049
- Seriously.
- Right.

124
00:07:18,354 --> 00:07:22,824
(Yun So realizes there may be
a significant age gap.)

125
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:30,765
(Will that change his feelings?)

126
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:32,967
This is so interesting.

127
00:07:33,336 --> 00:07:35,403
Yun So's photo was from a photo booth.

128
00:07:35,771 --> 00:07:37,739
- Excuse me?
- And Ju Hee's was taken on film.

129
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:39,308
We had photo booths back then too.

130
00:07:39,309 --> 00:07:40,675
- They had to be developed.
- Exactly.

131
00:07:40,676 --> 00:07:42,243
- They had to be developed.
- Come on.

132
00:07:42,244 --> 00:07:44,712
- That's hilarious.
- We had sticker photo booths too.

133
00:07:44,713 --> 00:07:46,914
You mean those sticker photos
where your face came out all blurry?

134
00:07:46,915 --> 00:07:49,283
- And the photos were tiny back then.
- Right.

135
00:07:49,284 --> 00:07:51,119
- And they took forever to print.
- Exactly.

136
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,453
- Let's stop.
- Okay.

137
00:07:54,357 --> 00:07:55,424
(The second day in Yeon House)

138
00:07:55,425 --> 00:07:56,558
Day Two.

139
00:07:59,028 --> 00:08:02,397
(Everyone experiences their first morning
together in Yeon House.)

140
00:08:05,935 --> 00:08:08,904
(The older women are still asleep even
after sunrise.)

141
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:11,506
(What about the younger men?)

142
00:08:12,475 --> 00:08:13,442
- Who's that?
- Who is it?

143
00:08:13,443 --> 00:08:14,342
(Alone in the kitchen)

144
00:08:14,343 --> 00:08:15,310
(It's Jin Woo.)

145
00:08:15,311 --> 00:08:16,578
- I knew it.
- Jin Woo.

146
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,081
The early bird Jin Woo will catch
the worm.

147
00:08:19,082 --> 00:08:22,117
(Making coffee)

148
00:08:22,551 --> 00:08:24,085
(Looking around)

149
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:29,925
(He takes an apron from the drawer.)

150
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:33,494
(Putting it on)

151
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:39,401
(He starts cleaning up the mess
from last night.)

152
00:08:39,869 --> 00:08:43,505
I don't think the level of affection
formed within six hours...

153
00:08:43,506 --> 00:08:46,242
of first meeting will determine
how things turn out in the future,

154
00:08:46,243 --> 00:08:48,944
so if I keep doing the dishes,
keep taking care of the recycling,

155
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:52,747
talk with the ladies a lot,
and continue going on dates together,

156
00:08:52,748 --> 00:08:54,449
I think they may gradually open
their hearts to me.

157
00:08:55,718 --> 00:08:57,886
He's right. He's so mature.

158
00:08:57,887 --> 00:08:59,888
I love how positive he is.

159
00:09:00,923 --> 00:09:03,691
(Hoping today will be better)

160
00:09:04,994 --> 00:09:08,897
(While enjoying his morning coffee...)

161
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:13,001
Someone's exercising.

162
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:14,870
(Jun Han is in the workout zone.)

163
00:09:14,871 --> 00:09:17,305
- It's Jun Han.
- The two contestants with zero votes!

164
00:09:18,441 --> 00:09:19,808
(After effortlessly setting up
the machine,)

165
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:24,246
(he fires up his workout.)

166
00:09:26,356 --> 00:09:30,152
He was really traumatized
by those results last night.

167
00:09:31,888 --> 00:09:33,788
I never lose confidence.

168
00:09:35,257 --> 00:09:36,924
If I show more of my serious side,

169
00:09:37,427 --> 00:09:40,595
I believe I can turn...

170
00:09:40,596 --> 00:09:41,930
things around.

171
00:09:42,532 --> 00:09:43,698
He's in incredible shape.

172
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,934
What does he do?

173
00:09:47,236 --> 00:09:53,341
(Training both body and mind
for a fresh start)

174
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:59,659
(Refreshed)

175
00:09:59,706 --> 00:10:04,122
Jun Han and Jin Woo are the opposite.

176
00:10:04,296 --> 00:10:06,484
- I know.
- Physically too.

177
00:10:06,651 --> 00:10:07,400
Style-wise as well.

178
00:10:08,049 --> 00:10:10,632
- And they both got zero votes.
- You shouldn't go to extremes.

179
00:10:10,656 --> 00:10:12,886
One is doing the dishes,
and the other is lifting weights.

180
00:10:12,887 --> 00:10:14,521
(They even process sadness
completely differently.)

181
00:10:14,855 --> 00:10:16,402
(Yu Jin and Ji Seung's room)

182
00:10:16,403 --> 00:10:17,894
She's up.

183
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:23,029
- Will I be able to run?
- Pardon?

184
00:10:23,325 --> 00:10:26,906
- I don't think I can.
- Are you really going to run?

185
00:10:28,354 --> 00:10:32,006
So, who's running tomorrow? Jun Han and...

186
00:10:32,112 --> 00:10:34,908
- My face will look different tomorrow.
- Mine too.

187
00:10:35,892 --> 00:10:39,673
- Let's pretend we don't notice.
- I'll wear sunglasses.

188
00:10:39,674 --> 00:10:41,314
They made a promise.

189
00:10:42,612 --> 00:10:44,084
Will Jun Han really workout?

190
00:10:47,854 --> 00:10:49,689
(Peeking out)

191
00:10:51,825 --> 00:10:53,004
He's waiting for her.

192
00:10:53,005 --> 00:10:56,363
(She spots Jun Han.)

193
00:10:57,099 --> 00:10:59,733
- He actually came out.
- He did?

194
00:11:00,945 --> 00:11:03,311
Good to see you again.

195
00:11:05,758 --> 00:11:09,342
- My goodness. That's crazy.
- That's crazy.

196
00:11:09,436 --> 00:11:10,811
He's indeed young.

197
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:14,114
I guess I should run.
I should keep my promise.

198
00:11:18,919 --> 00:11:21,655
(Jun Han starts running after stretching.)

199
00:11:22,615 --> 00:11:27,193
(Jogging around Yeon House)

200
00:11:31,327 --> 00:11:36,003
(He's running a lap around Yeon House.)

201
00:11:36,519 --> 00:11:40,479
- Is he there?
- I'm not sure. I'm going to check.

202
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,871
What time is it now?

203
00:11:44,285 --> 00:11:45,817
She's going outside.

204
00:11:46,302 --> 00:11:49,304
This is a good opportunity to talk.

205
00:11:49,591 --> 00:11:52,719
It's nice that they're doing that.

206
00:11:55,896 --> 00:11:58,358
(Unlike what she expected,
the workout zone is empty.)

207
00:12:00,435 --> 00:12:02,629
- Jun Han went back.
- What did you say?

208
00:12:02,749 --> 00:12:04,565
- He went back.
- He went back?

209
00:12:05,981 --> 00:12:07,441
(They didn't end up meeting.)

210
00:12:07,442 --> 00:12:08,442
Already?

211
00:12:09,536 --> 00:12:10,440
(Sad)

212
00:12:10,441 --> 00:12:12,387
- I guess he went back to get ready.
- I think so.

213
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:16,810
(Jun Han has already finished
and starts getting ready.)

214
00:12:16,899 --> 00:12:21,239
Goodness. That happened
because their places are separated.

215
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,916
That's true.

216
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:28,424
It was a good opportunity
for them to show off their charm.

217
00:12:32,735 --> 00:12:33,735
They got a message.

218
00:12:34,530 --> 00:12:35,730
What is it?

219
00:12:35,731 --> 00:12:37,831
(The younger men receive a message.)

220
00:12:38,131 --> 00:12:42,171
(Younger men, please gather
in the common area by 10 a.m.)

221
00:12:42,172 --> 00:12:44,471
(Younger men, please gather
in the common area by 10 a.m.)

222
00:12:45,138 --> 00:12:48,174
(The younger men get ready
and head to the common area.)

223
00:12:48,942 --> 00:12:50,243
(Nervous)

224
00:12:53,649 --> 00:12:59,252
(A mysterious envelope left
in the common area)

225
00:12:59,521 --> 00:13:02,128
- Shall we sit together?
- You should sit in the middle.

226
00:13:02,581 --> 00:13:03,581
It's like a family photo.

227
00:13:03,582 --> 00:13:05,192
(It's like a family photo arrangement.)

228
00:13:05,193 --> 00:13:07,394
(Sitting together)

229
00:13:07,761 --> 00:13:09,496
(Curious)

230
00:13:10,797 --> 00:13:16,002
(What's in the envelope?)

231
00:13:18,343 --> 00:13:19,606
Well...

232
00:13:20,395 --> 00:13:21,688
What is it?

233
00:13:22,202 --> 00:13:24,175
"Hold hands
with the older woman you like best."

234
00:13:24,921 --> 00:13:30,581
"Return to the common area
with the woman you like most for a date."

235
00:13:30,582 --> 00:13:32,582
"The older woman can't turn you down."

236
00:13:33,041 --> 00:13:36,291
- They have to get going now.
- They have to start running now.

237
00:13:36,423 --> 00:13:40,142
If someone takes your girl,
you can't hold her hand.

238
00:13:40,143 --> 00:13:43,936
I know. They should run over there now
and take a girl's hand.

239
00:13:44,509 --> 00:13:47,995
- "Hold hands with the older woman..."
- The common area?

240
00:13:48,548 --> 00:13:49,769
"First come, first served." I'm off!

241
00:13:50,234 --> 00:13:51,687
Jin Woo!

242
00:13:51,874 --> 00:13:55,114
- Jin Woo!
- Jin Woo is so enthusiastic.

243
00:13:55,134 --> 00:13:57,346
As he should be! He said he'd work harder.

244
00:13:57,508 --> 00:13:59,215
"First come, first served." I'm off!

245
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,220
You guys are so fast.

246
00:14:00,245 --> 00:14:02,005
(As it's first-come, first-served,
they don't even look back.)

247
00:14:02,582 --> 00:14:04,484
(We don't even have time to go back.)

248
00:14:04,952 --> 00:14:06,586
Yun So is such a manly man.

249
00:14:06,645 --> 00:14:09,444
They can do that
because they're younger men.

250
00:14:11,311 --> 00:14:13,105
- They're fast.
- They're running.

251
00:14:14,431 --> 00:14:17,090
Wait. I'm talking longer
because only I wore boots.

252
00:14:17,321 --> 00:14:18,532
You should run.

253
00:14:19,625 --> 00:14:22,435
(Yun So and Si Won rush
to the older women's rooms.)

254
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:27,363
It was first-come, first-served. I didn't
want to miss my chance for a date.

255
00:14:27,364 --> 00:14:28,642
I was the first one to run to their room.

256
00:14:30,256 --> 00:14:32,712
- Si Won likes Ji Seung.
- Ji Seung.

257
00:14:32,713 --> 00:14:34,881
(Si Won chose Ji Seung twice before.)

258
00:14:34,981 --> 00:14:35,981
Yes.

259
00:14:35,982 --> 00:14:38,054
(The older woman who made Si Won run)

260
00:14:38,055 --> 00:14:40,353
(It's Ji Seung again.)

261
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:44,024
Ji Seung, do you want to go
on a date with me?

262
00:14:44,025 --> 00:14:45,459
Yes.

263
00:14:45,587 --> 00:14:46,587
Take her hand!

264
00:14:47,419 --> 00:14:49,529
Hold hands! Otherwise, it doesn't count.

265
00:14:50,324 --> 00:14:52,523
Take my hand and come
to the common area with me.

266
00:14:52,547 --> 00:14:53,338
Do we have to hold hands?

267
00:14:53,339 --> 00:14:54,339
- Yes.
- Hold hands?

268
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:58,371
I'll be waiting outside,
so whenever you're ready...

269
00:14:58,768 --> 00:15:01,241
- Do you want to change?
- I'll go change.

270
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:05,912
I'm surprised.

271
00:15:07,113 --> 00:15:08,620
We have to hold hands
on the way to the common area?

272
00:15:10,066 --> 00:15:12,418
I think Si Won just said that
because he wanted to.

273
00:15:14,866 --> 00:15:15,866
Is he joking?

274
00:15:15,867 --> 00:15:17,290
(While they're misunderstanding Si Won)

275
00:15:17,879 --> 00:15:21,461
(Another younger man, Yun So,
who rushed out)

276
00:15:21,935 --> 00:15:23,809
I didn't even think twice
and went for Ju Hee.

277
00:15:24,895 --> 00:15:26,165
Yun So!

278
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:28,068
(In a hurry)

279
00:15:29,425 --> 00:15:31,345
- Is Ju Hee in there?
- Yes.

280
00:15:33,606 --> 00:15:35,608
(Me?)

281
00:15:36,057 --> 00:15:37,277
Ju Hee, go on a date with me.

282
00:15:37,683 --> 00:15:40,049
That's something a younger man would say.

283
00:15:40,050 --> 00:15:42,783
He sounds different, right?
That's different from what Si Won said.

284
00:15:43,516 --> 00:15:44,686
Ju Hee, go on a date with me.

285
00:15:44,687 --> 00:15:47,421
(Yun So asks Ju Hee out
while she's still in the room.)

286
00:15:47,422 --> 00:15:48,422
Okay.

287
00:15:48,746 --> 00:15:49,746
- Okay.
- With me.

288
00:15:50,639 --> 00:15:52,729
- Okay. We should go now.
- Now?

289
00:15:53,382 --> 00:15:55,382
- To the common area now.
- Right now?

290
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:57,063
- Are you joking?
- I'm serious.

291
00:15:57,064 --> 00:15:58,364
(Ji Hye is listening to what's happening.)

292
00:15:58,798 --> 00:16:02,468
(Last night, Ji Hye also sent
Yun So a Love QR.)

293
00:16:02,536 --> 00:16:05,605
Yun So came over and looked for Ju Hee.

294
00:16:06,206 --> 00:16:10,236
I thought, "I guess I wasn't chosen."

295
00:16:12,421 --> 00:16:13,913
- We're matching.
- Are you serious?

296
00:16:13,938 --> 00:16:15,825
- Matching outfits.
- Yes. For real.

297
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:18,452
(Ju Hee and Yun So hold hands
for the first time.)

298
00:16:18,718 --> 00:16:21,955
(It even makes her heart flutter.)

299
00:16:23,634 --> 00:16:25,287
- The photo couple.
- Should we go that way?

300
00:16:25,586 --> 00:16:26,586
Yes.

301
00:16:27,371 --> 00:16:29,329
- What time did you go to sleep?
- I barely slept.

302
00:16:29,587 --> 00:16:30,587
What time?

303
00:16:30,612 --> 00:16:33,366
(He doesn't let go
even while switching hands.)

304
00:16:33,801 --> 00:16:36,236
I didn't expect to hold hands.

305
00:16:37,084 --> 00:16:38,084
It gave me butterflies.

306
00:16:40,203 --> 00:16:42,809
- The timing might be off.
- I know.

307
00:16:45,242 --> 00:16:47,089
I went straight to you
so no one else would take you.

308
00:16:48,352 --> 00:16:49,352
That's impressive.

309
00:16:50,632 --> 00:16:56,256
(Now Jin Woo and Jun Han are left.)

310
00:16:57,987 --> 00:17:00,960
(Jun Han?)

311
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:05,432
(These two sent a Love QR
to the same person.)

312
00:17:05,651 --> 00:17:08,935
(That person was Ji Hye.)

313
00:17:10,045 --> 00:17:15,108
Ask her out now.
You shouldn't be hesitating.

314
00:17:15,109 --> 00:17:16,142
(Nervous)

315
00:17:18,843 --> 00:17:21,667
If you need more time, I'll wait outside.
Go on a date with me.

316
00:17:21,923 --> 00:17:25,285
- He asked her out.
- Good job.

317
00:17:25,723 --> 00:17:28,121
- Go on a date with me.
- Are you talking to me?

318
00:17:28,595 --> 00:17:30,657
I thought you were talking to Ju Hee.

319
00:17:30,710 --> 00:17:33,194
- No, I came for you. Can you go now?
- Really? I'll be quick.

320
00:17:33,428 --> 00:17:35,595
- Do we have to go now? Wait.
- Take your time.

321
00:17:38,346 --> 00:17:40,466
I only thought of Ji Hye.

322
00:17:41,133 --> 00:17:42,669
I hope they work out.

323
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:46,106
(Jin Woo has been interested in Ji Hye
since last night.)

324
00:17:46,406 --> 00:17:49,072
- I'm not kidding. We should hold hands.
- Really?

325
00:17:50,624 --> 00:17:53,378
- Do we really have to hold hands?
- I'll show you the card later.

326
00:17:54,523 --> 00:17:56,569
- They look good together.
- They do.

327
00:17:56,571 --> 00:17:59,118
- They make a good couple.
- They're cute.

328
00:17:59,909 --> 00:18:01,743
- You two look hot together.
- Right?

329
00:18:02,989 --> 00:18:04,958
(Bitter)

330
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:06,792
He said we should hold hands.

331
00:18:06,793 --> 00:18:08,828
I thought he was joking.

332
00:18:09,951 --> 00:18:11,358
I liked holding hands with him.

333
00:18:11,864 --> 00:18:13,899
(Shy)

334
00:18:14,637 --> 00:18:16,910
- Am I sweating or is that you?
- You.

335
00:18:16,957 --> 00:18:18,938
- I think so.
- Are you nervous?

336
00:18:20,635 --> 00:18:21,902
I haven't held a woman's hand in a while.

337
00:18:23,509 --> 00:18:25,778
Jin Woo has nice shoulders.

338
00:18:27,149 --> 00:18:30,750
- It's cute that we have to hold hands.
- It really says that.

339
00:18:32,152 --> 00:18:36,990
(Jun Han looked at Ji Hye
with a mysterious expression.)

340
00:18:38,537 --> 00:18:40,537
- What's up?
- Is Yu Jin here?

341
00:18:40,538 --> 00:18:44,660
- She is.
- Hey, I went outside and didn't see you.

342
00:18:45,661 --> 00:18:48,704
- Do you want to go out with me today?
- A date?

343
00:18:48,705 --> 00:18:51,784
- Yu Jin.
- Yes.

344
00:18:51,785 --> 00:18:52,924
- See you later.
- Okay.

345
00:18:52,925 --> 00:18:54,441
(Jun Han asked Yu Jin out.)

346
00:18:55,476 --> 00:18:59,112
I got so shy
that my cheekbones started to tremble.

347
00:19:01,288 --> 00:19:04,784
The girls I wanted to ask out
and get to know...

348
00:19:05,381 --> 00:19:07,831
were Ji Hye and Yu Jin.

349
00:19:08,517 --> 00:19:11,997
I was glad that I got
to know Yu Jin first.

350
00:19:13,756 --> 00:19:18,494
- That's good.
- Did he change his mind,

351
00:19:18,495 --> 00:19:21,067
- or did he want Ji Hye first?
- We'll never know.

352
00:19:22,172 --> 00:19:24,865
- Shall we go?
- Really? Do we have to hold hands?

353
00:19:24,866 --> 00:19:26,568
Yes, everyone held hands.

354
00:19:27,346 --> 00:19:29,075
Gosh. That's crazy!

355
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:31,877
They really look good together.

356
00:19:31,878 --> 00:19:33,020
(Si Won and Ji Seung)

357
00:19:33,021 --> 00:19:34,847
- We have to hold hands?
- We do.

358
00:19:36,134 --> 00:19:39,953
(They're awkward and shy
but are holding hands.)

359
00:19:40,046 --> 00:19:41,854
- Here.
- Oh, my.

360
00:19:42,889 --> 00:19:43,612
(Jun Han and Yu Jin)

361
00:19:43,613 --> 00:19:45,425
Jun Han seems really nice.

362
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:47,126
- I'm a little shy.
- Me too.

363
00:19:50,165 --> 00:19:52,624
It had been a while.
It really made my heart flutter.

364
00:19:53,664 --> 00:19:56,702
When I held her soft hand,

365
00:19:57,230 --> 00:19:59,506
It gave me butterflies right away.

366
00:20:00,218 --> 00:20:02,251
I got butterflies again.

367
00:20:03,818 --> 00:20:05,285
By the way, did you go running?

368
00:20:05,818 --> 00:20:06,985
I was going to,

369
00:20:06,985 --> 00:20:10,251
but I just did
a 30-minute interval workout.

370
00:20:10,251 --> 00:20:11,251
Why didn't you tell me?

371
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:14,485
I came out, but you weren't there.
I got startled.

372
00:20:14,485 --> 00:20:17,151
You all slept late
but had to wake up early.

373
00:20:17,151 --> 00:20:18,151
I wanted you to rest a bit more.

374
00:20:18,751 --> 00:20:19,851
So I didn't tell you on purpose.

375
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:20,918
(Clearing up the misunderstanding)

376
00:20:21,685 --> 00:20:22,885
I guess we are cooking.

377
00:20:22,885 --> 00:20:23,918
I think so.

378
00:20:23,918 --> 00:20:26,485
(The couples are all matched
for their first date.)

379
00:20:26,618 --> 00:20:30,885
I'm starting to like Yun So more and more.

380
00:20:30,885 --> 00:20:32,218
Isn't he so attractive?

381
00:20:32,218 --> 00:20:35,085
He jumped over the couch on his way out.

382
00:20:35,585 --> 00:20:37,085
- That's what I liked about him.
- Right.

383
00:20:37,585 --> 00:20:39,651
Just watching them makes me happy.

384
00:20:39,651 --> 00:20:41,585
Imagine how much the women loved it.

385
00:20:41,585 --> 00:20:44,551
- The women's steps were so light.
- Exactly.

386
00:20:44,551 --> 00:20:45,551
No!

387
00:20:45,551 --> 00:20:47,818
- How did they walk then?
- The women...

388
00:20:47,818 --> 00:20:49,485
were walking on air.

389
00:20:50,118 --> 00:20:51,551
(You're unbelievable!)

390
00:20:51,685 --> 00:20:53,051
- They were flying.
- Yes.

391
00:20:53,051 --> 00:20:55,118
They were floating in the air.

392
00:20:55,118 --> 00:20:56,451
Basically drones.

393
00:20:57,851 --> 00:21:00,251
This is too sudden.
We could barely prepare.

394
00:21:00,251 --> 00:21:02,118
It might seem strange to them.

395
00:21:02,751 --> 00:21:04,185
But it's obvious.

396
00:21:04,185 --> 00:21:05,918
You can tell who the guys are into...

397
00:21:05,918 --> 00:21:08,918
- in that common area.
- You're right.

398
00:21:11,318 --> 00:21:13,218
Oh, are you newlyweds?

399
00:21:14,151 --> 00:21:15,218
(Just happy)

400
00:21:15,218 --> 00:21:16,585
Everyone looks excited.

401
00:21:17,685 --> 00:21:18,951
Did you expect me to choose you?

402
00:21:19,351 --> 00:21:20,351
I didn't.

403
00:21:20,351 --> 00:21:21,485
- Really?
- Yes.

404
00:21:21,485 --> 00:21:25,385
You didn't think it was me
even from the Love QR last night?

405
00:21:26,218 --> 00:21:27,718
But it was only...

406
00:21:28,318 --> 00:21:29,551
braised kimchi.

407
00:21:29,551 --> 00:21:30,551
That's right.

408
00:21:31,385 --> 00:21:34,518
(They made braised kimchi together
on the first night.)

409
00:21:35,551 --> 00:21:38,385
(Yun So sent the Love QR...)

410
00:21:38,385 --> 00:21:41,551
(filled with the memories they shared.)

411
00:21:41,751 --> 00:21:43,718
- I didn't recognize you.
- You didn't?

412
00:21:45,185 --> 00:21:46,985
- Did you see the QR last night?
- Yes.

413
00:21:47,651 --> 00:21:48,651
Did you know it was me?

414
00:21:49,818 --> 00:21:53,218
(Ju Hee also sent a Love QR to Yun So.)

415
00:21:53,551 --> 00:21:54,751
Was it about taking a walk?

416
00:21:54,751 --> 00:21:55,751
Yes.

417
00:21:56,318 --> 00:21:57,385
What a relief.

418
00:21:57,651 --> 00:22:00,785
(He just won't stop smiling.)

419
00:22:00,785 --> 00:22:02,018
I was hoping you'd send it to me.

420
00:22:02,018 --> 00:22:04,885
- I'm glad I got it.
- Good.

421
00:22:05,151 --> 00:22:06,851
It's nice just watching them.

422
00:22:06,851 --> 00:22:07,851
What are you wearing today?

423
00:22:08,151 --> 00:22:10,118
Today? I'll just wear...

424
00:22:10,118 --> 00:22:13,018
a gray cardigan and a beige skirt?

425
00:22:13,018 --> 00:22:14,651
- A gray cardigan and a beige skirt?
- Yes.

426
00:22:15,551 --> 00:22:16,818
- Okay, beige.
- Are you matching with me?

427
00:22:16,818 --> 00:22:17,818
I will.

428
00:22:18,618 --> 00:22:19,785
Do you like matching clothes?

429
00:22:19,785 --> 00:22:20,785
I do.

430
00:22:21,651 --> 00:22:23,118
I like matching too.

431
00:22:23,118 --> 00:22:24,451
Matching outfits.

432
00:22:24,918 --> 00:22:25,951
I'll look forward to it.

433
00:22:25,951 --> 00:22:26,951
(Ears perked up)

434
00:22:27,244 --> 00:22:28,444
Should we match our outfits too?

435
00:22:28,851 --> 00:22:30,485
Sure. What are you wearing?

436
00:22:30,485 --> 00:22:31,518
Do you have a sky blue shirt?

437
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:34,151
- I have a blue one.
- That's great.

438
00:22:34,151 --> 00:22:35,418
A blue shirt with jeans?

439
00:22:35,418 --> 00:22:36,418
Good idea.

440
00:22:36,418 --> 00:22:38,151
- That sounds nice.
- I'll try them on.

441
00:22:39,051 --> 00:22:40,051
Let me give them a try.

442
00:22:41,018 --> 00:22:44,451
(Yu Jin and Jun Han already look excited.)

443
00:22:44,451 --> 00:22:45,985
For first impressions,

444
00:22:46,918 --> 00:22:48,851
I like people with a beautiful smile.

445
00:22:49,485 --> 00:22:50,785
You smile just like me.

446
00:22:50,785 --> 00:22:52,351
Yes, I like your smile.

447
00:22:52,351 --> 00:22:54,251
They both kept smiling but got zero votes.

448
00:22:54,251 --> 00:22:55,451
(True!)

449
00:22:55,451 --> 00:22:57,385
They're exactly alike.

450
00:22:57,885 --> 00:22:59,018
I'm just like you.

451
00:22:59,518 --> 00:23:01,751
I liked the way you smiled
when we first met.

452
00:23:03,685 --> 00:23:04,785
So I voted for you.

453
00:23:05,485 --> 00:23:07,785
(They chose each other
in the first-impression vote...)

454
00:23:07,785 --> 00:23:10,118
(but sent their Love QRs
to different people.)

455
00:23:11,118 --> 00:23:13,085
Let's start over then.

456
00:23:13,585 --> 00:23:14,985
We'll get to know each other again.

457
00:23:14,985 --> 00:23:16,018
I'm fine with it.

458
00:23:17,185 --> 00:23:18,185
Beige.

459
00:23:18,185 --> 00:23:20,785
(After deciding on matching outfits,
they go back to get ready for their date.)

460
00:23:22,951 --> 00:23:23,985
Hi!

461
00:23:24,485 --> 00:23:25,551
Nice to see you.

462
00:23:26,985 --> 00:23:27,985
(Jun Han is overly excited.)

463
00:23:27,985 --> 00:23:29,851
Oh, my!

464
00:23:29,851 --> 00:23:30,918
I should change.

465
00:23:31,218 --> 00:23:32,585
He's so excited!

466
00:23:32,585 --> 00:23:33,585
(Staring)

467
00:23:34,251 --> 00:23:35,585
But why did you take your time?

468
00:23:36,485 --> 00:23:37,485
- Me?
- Yes.

469
00:23:38,518 --> 00:23:39,818
I told you I liked two people yesterday.

470
00:23:40,185 --> 00:23:41,185
Were you a little torn?

471
00:23:41,685 --> 00:23:42,851
Because there were two,

472
00:23:42,851 --> 00:23:44,851
I wanted to get to know both of them.

473
00:23:45,651 --> 00:23:47,585
So I was fine with either one.

474
00:23:50,118 --> 00:23:52,585
They picked the same person yesterday.

475
00:23:53,751 --> 00:23:54,751
How was it...

476
00:23:55,418 --> 00:23:56,551
when you talked to Ji Hye?

477
00:23:57,751 --> 00:23:58,751
I liked it.

478
00:23:59,185 --> 00:24:00,985
I never thought you'd go to Ji Hye.

479
00:24:00,985 --> 00:24:02,485
I did what I wanted to do.

480
00:24:02,718 --> 00:24:04,485
What's with this atmosphere?

481
00:24:07,185 --> 00:24:08,185
It's a bit tense.

482
00:24:08,185 --> 00:24:09,818
- There's some tension right now.
- Yes.

483
00:24:09,818 --> 00:24:11,718
(A subtle tension between the two)

484
00:24:12,751 --> 00:24:14,851
My biggest threat is...

485
00:24:14,851 --> 00:24:18,985
Jun Han, my roommate.

486
00:24:18,985 --> 00:24:21,385
He's more masculine than I am,

487
00:24:21,685 --> 00:24:23,718
and as for his physique,

488
00:24:23,718 --> 00:24:25,818
he has a build that women would like.

489
00:24:26,151 --> 00:24:29,851
So if he's interested in Ji Hye,

490
00:24:30,851 --> 00:24:32,718
it would bother me, of course.

491
00:24:33,051 --> 00:24:35,318
Right. For Jin Woo,

492
00:24:35,318 --> 00:24:37,718
Jun Han is completely different from him.

493
00:24:37,718 --> 00:24:40,185
He's got something he doesn't have,

494
00:24:40,185 --> 00:24:42,151
- so he'd find him as a huge threat.
- You're right.

495
00:24:42,585 --> 00:24:43,785
I'll just match the beige pants only.

496
00:24:44,651 --> 00:24:47,418
We also talked
about wearing matching outfits.

497
00:24:52,818 --> 00:24:55,351
Wow, look at his body!

498
00:24:55,351 --> 00:24:56,651
Jin Woo just lost.

499
00:24:56,651 --> 00:24:57,751
(Laughing)

500
00:24:57,751 --> 00:24:59,551
- It's one to zero.
- He didn't even fight, but still lost.

501
00:25:00,351 --> 00:25:01,493
(Yu Jin and Jun Han are first
for the date.)

502
00:25:01,518 --> 00:25:02,418
I'm sorry.

503
00:25:02,418 --> 00:25:03,451
It's okay.

504
00:25:05,151 --> 00:25:08,018
Actually, I only matched my pants today.

505
00:25:08,018 --> 00:25:09,851
- He matched with her?
- Yes, he did.

506
00:25:09,851 --> 00:25:11,318
It might be a bit much for the tops.

507
00:25:11,985 --> 00:25:13,118
All right.

508
00:25:13,485 --> 00:25:15,285
Wow, that looks beautiful!

509
00:25:15,718 --> 00:25:17,618
If we go on a date next time,

510
00:25:18,085 --> 00:25:19,851
let's match everything.

511
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:20,851
Okay.

512
00:25:21,185 --> 00:25:23,718
Do you think we have the same clothes?

513
00:25:24,218 --> 00:25:25,218
The same clothes?

514
00:25:25,218 --> 00:25:27,451
- I'll try my best to match yours.
- You will?

515
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:31,885
(They plan to take Jun Han's car.)

516
00:25:34,585 --> 00:25:35,818
It's not open!

517
00:25:36,151 --> 00:25:38,418
(The door shuts carelessly...)

518
00:25:38,418 --> 00:25:39,685
(with a soft thud.)

519
00:25:39,685 --> 00:25:40,685
I was feeling shy.

520
00:25:41,585 --> 00:25:42,951
- Let me open it again.
- This is so funny!

521
00:25:43,251 --> 00:25:44,451
- I was shy.
- Thank you!

522
00:25:44,818 --> 00:25:45,818
Tissues.

523
00:25:46,551 --> 00:25:47,951
There are tissues.

524
00:25:48,218 --> 00:25:50,385
- I was too shy to open it properly.
- Good.

525
00:25:50,385 --> 00:25:52,851
- I'll open it again next time.
- No, it's fine.

526
00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:53,851
(How cute.)

527
00:25:53,851 --> 00:25:55,018
He's cute.

528
00:25:55,985 --> 00:25:58,185
(Feeling awkward)

529
00:25:59,985 --> 00:26:00,985
So funny.

530
00:26:02,551 --> 00:26:03,951
(Oh, man.)

531
00:26:04,151 --> 00:26:05,318
- Shall we go now?
- Yes.

532
00:26:06,118 --> 00:26:07,285
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

533
00:26:07,285 --> 00:26:10,051
I can't wait to watch Jun Han's date.

534
00:26:10,051 --> 00:26:11,885
- I'll drive safely.
- Okay.

535
00:26:13,485 --> 00:26:14,551
- Time to talk!
- Sure.

536
00:26:14,551 --> 00:26:15,718
This is the Talk Room.

537
00:26:15,718 --> 00:26:18,618
We normally talk a lot in a car.

538
00:26:18,618 --> 00:26:19,618
That's right.

539
00:26:19,618 --> 00:26:21,685
We get closer when we talk in a car.

540
00:26:22,551 --> 00:26:25,051
I like listening to my favorite songs
and talking about them.

541
00:26:25,051 --> 00:26:27,518
I also love conversations in a car.

542
00:26:28,851 --> 00:26:29,851
But...

543
00:26:30,118 --> 00:26:31,785
does age matter in a relationship?

544
00:26:32,151 --> 00:26:34,151
(Shaking)

545
00:26:34,585 --> 00:26:35,918
(Gently)

546
00:26:35,918 --> 00:26:36,918
Goodness!

547
00:26:37,151 --> 00:26:39,451
(Shy)

548
00:26:39,951 --> 00:26:41,818
Is this a younger man's charm?

549
00:26:45,518 --> 00:26:46,518
How about that?

550
00:26:46,518 --> 00:26:49,751
Based on the way
he naturally tries to protect her,

551
00:26:50,285 --> 00:26:51,285
he's pretty smooth.

552
00:26:51,418 --> 00:26:52,751
Honestly, that comes from experience.

553
00:26:53,185 --> 00:26:54,951
- It's pure experience.
- He's done that before.

554
00:26:56,218 --> 00:26:58,718
- One thing is for sure.
- What?

555
00:26:58,718 --> 00:27:01,818
If you go on a date with me,

556
00:27:02,418 --> 00:27:05,918
you'll have a spectacular
and fun relationship.

557
00:27:05,918 --> 00:27:07,485
Really? Like what?

558
00:27:07,485 --> 00:27:08,485
For example,

559
00:27:08,751 --> 00:27:10,585
I like playing pranks.

560
00:27:11,585 --> 00:27:16,051
And people often tell me
I pull some clever ones.

561
00:27:16,051 --> 00:27:17,085
(Impressed)

562
00:27:17,085 --> 00:27:19,185
Pranks others wouldn't think of.

563
00:27:19,185 --> 00:27:20,551
- Pranks others wouldn't think of?
- Yes.

564
00:27:20,551 --> 00:27:21,551
I'm so curious.

565
00:27:21,885 --> 00:27:23,551
Do you often play pranks
on your girlfriend?

566
00:27:23,551 --> 00:27:25,151
- A lot.
- You do?

567
00:27:26,718 --> 00:27:30,451
I like it when she plays along
and we prank each other.

568
00:27:30,985 --> 00:27:32,585
What if she gets serious?

569
00:27:32,585 --> 00:27:33,885
Then I'd say, "Sorry."

570
00:27:33,885 --> 00:27:35,718
"Can you forgive me?"

571
00:27:35,718 --> 00:27:36,818
And you stop?

572
00:27:37,351 --> 00:27:38,718
"I won't do it again. That's my mistake."

573
00:27:38,718 --> 00:27:39,785
"That's my mistake!"

574
00:27:40,618 --> 00:27:42,351
I wonder what kind of prank it is.

575
00:27:43,151 --> 00:27:44,918
I might show you
little by little later on.

576
00:27:44,918 --> 00:27:47,085
- If you get more comfortable?
- Yes.

577
00:27:47,085 --> 00:27:48,085
Cute!

578
00:27:48,085 --> 00:27:49,318
I didn't know he had that charm.

579
00:27:49,318 --> 00:27:50,785
They look good together.

580
00:27:50,785 --> 00:27:52,251
They won't stop smiling.

581
00:27:53,618 --> 00:27:56,951
What do you think
about men and women being just friends?

582
00:27:56,951 --> 00:27:57,951
For me,

583
00:27:58,418 --> 00:28:02,951
I don't have a friend of the opposite sex.

584
00:28:03,718 --> 00:28:04,718
You really don't have any?

585
00:28:06,485 --> 00:28:10,451
For those I meet through work,
I treat them as older women,

586
00:28:10,451 --> 00:28:15,285
but that doesn't mean
I like them because they're older.

587
00:28:15,951 --> 00:28:19,118
When I treat them as older women,
I don't see them in a romantic way.

588
00:28:19,118 --> 00:28:20,718
- They're just friends?
- Yes.

589
00:28:21,685 --> 00:28:23,918
But if I call someone by their name,

590
00:28:25,585 --> 00:28:27,518
I see them as a romantic interest.

591
00:28:27,885 --> 00:28:29,085
- That's why...
- Then...

592
00:28:29,085 --> 00:28:30,418
you do that
even if they're ten years older?

593
00:28:30,418 --> 00:28:32,018
- Yes.
- Really?

594
00:28:32,585 --> 00:28:34,085
But for that,

595
00:28:34,418 --> 00:28:35,751
I call them by their names at first...

596
00:28:36,318 --> 00:28:39,285
and switch to nicknames later.

597
00:28:40,351 --> 00:28:41,751
- Nicknames?
- Nicknames.

598
00:28:42,885 --> 00:28:45,018
I describe people using food.

599
00:28:45,018 --> 00:28:46,051
Really?

600
00:28:46,051 --> 00:28:47,085
For instance, I'd say,

601
00:28:47,951 --> 00:28:49,318
"You look like a Dubai chewy cookie."

602
00:28:49,685 --> 00:28:51,218
Like a Dubai chewy cookie?

603
00:28:51,218 --> 00:28:52,351
(Bursting out laughing)

604
00:28:52,685 --> 00:28:53,985
There are some similarities.

605
00:28:54,651 --> 00:28:57,251
Dubai chewy cookies are round and cute.

606
00:28:57,251 --> 00:28:58,751
"You look cute just like that."

607
00:28:59,251 --> 00:29:00,451
I would say that.

608
00:29:00,751 --> 00:29:02,618
What do I look like?

609
00:29:03,551 --> 00:29:06,485
(Glancing)

610
00:29:07,218 --> 00:29:09,451
- A white chocolate ball.
- A white chocolate ball!

611
00:29:12,951 --> 00:29:15,251
I hate that I know what you mean!

612
00:29:15,251 --> 00:29:16,251
Am I right?

613
00:29:16,518 --> 00:29:18,118
Have you met anyone
who makes nicknames like this?

614
00:29:18,118 --> 00:29:19,418
Not at all.

615
00:29:19,718 --> 00:29:22,918
Let's give everyone nicknames
when we get back.

616
00:29:22,918 --> 00:29:25,618
- I don't usually give them, though.
- You don't?

617
00:29:26,618 --> 00:29:30,918
I only give nicknames
to people I'm really interested in.

618
00:29:31,251 --> 00:29:33,618
Otherwise, I don't tend to give them one.

619
00:29:35,151 --> 00:29:37,818
- A white chocolate ball!
- Isn't that creative?

620
00:29:37,818 --> 00:29:39,685
This will stick with me today.

621
00:29:40,251 --> 00:29:41,251
I did it.

622
00:29:42,318 --> 00:29:43,518
A white chocolate ball.

623
00:29:44,885 --> 00:29:46,485
There was other food,

624
00:29:46,485 --> 00:29:47,885
but I wanted to say
that she looked round...

625
00:29:48,451 --> 00:29:54,285
and elegant like a white chocolate ball.

626
00:29:54,585 --> 00:29:58,518
So I gave Yu Jin a nickname
for the first time.

627
00:29:59,452 --> 00:30:02,176
The two click better than I thought.

628
00:30:02,645 --> 00:30:05,546
Some older women love
such flirting out of nowhere.

629
00:30:07,516 --> 00:30:08,583
Oh, look. Cherry blossoms.

630
00:30:08,984 --> 00:30:09,984
I saw them.

631
00:30:09,985 --> 00:30:11,919
You're the first woman
I've ever seen cherry blossoms with.

632
00:30:12,555 --> 00:30:13,655
Seriously, you're the first.

633
00:30:13,656 --> 00:30:14,523
Really?

634
00:30:14,524 --> 00:30:15,423
Me too!

635
00:30:16,493 --> 00:30:17,959
It's the same for me too.

636
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,661
(Great chemistry)

637
00:30:19,662 --> 00:30:21,096
They actually seem so alike.

638
00:30:21,097 --> 00:30:21,930
Right.

639
00:30:21,931 --> 00:30:23,932
(Their smiles and even their personalities
seem similar.)

640
00:30:24,366 --> 00:30:26,268
(Ju Hee and Yun So head out
on their date.)

641
00:30:26,269 --> 00:30:27,301
I'll take the bag.

642
00:30:27,803 --> 00:30:29,036
I'll put it in the back seat.

643
00:30:29,271 --> 00:30:30,101
- I'll do it for you.
- Okay.

644
00:30:30,374 --> 00:30:34,642
(Yun So isn't confident behind the wheel,
so he takes the passenger seat.)

645
00:30:35,044 --> 00:30:36,578
If the car is big,
I'm even worse at driving.

646
00:30:37,079 --> 00:30:38,513
I used to drive an SUV.

647
00:30:38,514 --> 00:30:40,014
That really scares me.

648
00:30:40,583 --> 00:30:42,183
My first car was an SUV.

649
00:30:42,952 --> 00:30:44,519
So Yun So says he can't drive very well.

650
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:45,989
Does he not drive, or is he just bad?

651
00:30:46,014 --> 00:30:47,421
Maybe he's just a little out of practice.

652
00:30:51,727 --> 00:30:53,428
(An older woman's charisma)

653
00:30:53,429 --> 00:30:54,362
So cool.

654
00:30:54,363 --> 00:30:55,797
(Peeking)

655
00:30:57,399 --> 00:30:59,333
(Ju Hee takes control of the car
with ease.)

656
00:30:59,702 --> 00:31:01,836
Seeing everyone else drive makes me feel
a little self-conscious.

657
00:31:02,410 --> 00:31:03,844
Don't worry.

658
00:31:05,140 --> 00:31:07,308
(Feeling small)

659
00:31:07,309 --> 00:31:08,676
I feel like I'm the only one
who can't drive.

660
00:31:08,877 --> 00:31:09,577
(Finding him cute)

661
00:31:09,578 --> 00:31:10,778
It's okay. You've got me.

662
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:13,814
- I'll be the only one who never drives.
- I really love driving.

663
00:31:14,283 --> 00:31:15,149
Really?

664
00:31:19,021 --> 00:31:21,089
Then I'll make sure you don't get bored
for the next 30 minutes.

665
00:31:21,090 --> 00:31:21,889
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

666
00:31:24,126 --> 00:31:25,359
- Let's go.
- Okay.

667
00:31:26,261 --> 00:31:28,128
- Right turn. Let's go.
- Okay.

668
00:31:30,099 --> 00:31:30,965
It's going to be fun.

669
00:31:31,067 --> 00:31:32,733
- The weather is lovely.
- I know.

670
00:31:32,734 --> 00:31:34,936
(The date begins with the older woman
behind the wheel.)

671
00:31:35,838 --> 00:31:36,704
You're so cool.

672
00:31:37,239 --> 00:31:38,139
Am I?

673
00:31:38,774 --> 00:31:40,341
I really admire people
who are good at things...

674
00:31:40,342 --> 00:31:41,342
I'm not good at.

675
00:31:41,343 --> 00:31:42,777
Right. You said that yesterday.

676
00:31:42,778 --> 00:31:43,745
- You remember?
- Yes.

677
00:31:44,513 --> 00:31:46,614
(Excited)

678
00:31:47,282 --> 00:31:50,585
I really like it
when an older woman drives.

679
00:31:50,586 --> 00:31:51,518
Really?

680
00:31:51,988 --> 00:31:54,089
Do you find it attractive
when an older woman is behind the wheel?

681
00:31:54,090 --> 00:31:55,990
Attractive enough to fall in love.

682
00:31:56,792 --> 00:31:57,725
Seriously?

683
00:31:57,726 --> 00:32:00,461
Especially when I'm not very confident
at driving,

684
00:32:00,629 --> 00:32:02,697
but she's completely comfortable with it.

685
00:32:03,265 --> 00:32:05,700
Seeing that makes it impossible
not to fall for her.

686
00:32:06,468 --> 00:32:08,068
What kind of woman are you attracted to?

687
00:32:08,971 --> 00:32:11,005
I like a woman who's elegant...

688
00:32:12,141 --> 00:32:13,041
and has a beautiful smile.

689
00:32:14,309 --> 00:32:15,876
(Glancing)

690
00:32:17,079 --> 00:32:18,112
And you have a beautiful smile.

691
00:32:21,416 --> 00:32:23,550
(Smiling)

692
00:32:24,153 --> 00:32:25,553
By the way, do you think...

693
00:32:26,355 --> 00:32:28,890
my hair looked better curly yesterday
or today with it completely down?

694
00:32:29,291 --> 00:32:32,394
I think today's hairstyle looks better.

695
00:32:32,395 --> 00:32:33,395
- Today's hairstyle?
- Yes.

696
00:32:34,163 --> 00:32:35,263
But I liked yesterday's too.

697
00:32:36,765 --> 00:32:37,865
I want to go with the one you prefer.

698
00:32:38,134 --> 00:32:40,068
I think today's style looks better.

699
00:32:41,871 --> 00:32:43,404
Short hair really suits you.

700
00:32:44,073 --> 00:32:46,708
If I'd known that,
I'd have cut it short much sooner.

701
00:32:49,344 --> 00:32:50,144
(Peeking)

702
00:32:50,746 --> 00:32:53,281
(Shy)

703
00:32:53,282 --> 00:32:54,349
The two look so good together.

704
00:32:54,350 --> 00:32:56,017
There's such a fluttery vibe between them.

705
00:32:57,953 --> 00:33:00,821
Can I ask who you picked
for the First Impression?

706
00:33:00,822 --> 00:33:02,356
Are we allowed to reveal that?

707
00:33:02,891 --> 00:33:04,492
I think it's fine if I share mine too.

708
00:33:04,493 --> 00:33:06,026
- Then should we?
- Gosh.

709
00:33:06,027 --> 00:33:08,830
I picked you.

710
00:33:08,831 --> 00:33:09,930
- Really?
- Yes.

711
00:33:10,466 --> 00:33:12,634
Really?

712
00:33:13,135 --> 00:33:14,435
(Touched)

713
00:33:16,672 --> 00:33:20,408
I see.

714
00:33:21,543 --> 00:33:22,443
I picked you as well.

715
00:33:22,745 --> 00:33:23,611
Really?

716
00:33:24,780 --> 00:33:26,180
I picked you.

717
00:33:27,116 --> 00:33:29,250
You were sitting close to me,

718
00:33:29,251 --> 00:33:34,022
and I felt like we'd get along the best.

719
00:33:35,124 --> 00:33:36,624
I was curious about you.

720
00:33:36,893 --> 00:33:40,295
At first, I thought
you were a really quiet person.

721
00:33:40,296 --> 00:33:42,630
- Me?
- That's why...

722
00:33:42,631 --> 00:33:44,265
I kept following you around
while we were cooking.

723
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,667
Really? I had no idea.

724
00:33:47,970 --> 00:33:50,305
(The night before,)

725
00:33:50,306 --> 00:33:53,441
(Yun So kept hovering around Ju Hee.)

726
00:33:53,442 --> 00:33:54,866
I tried to stay close to you
as much as possible.

727
00:33:54,891 --> 00:33:55,677
You did?

728
00:33:56,879 --> 00:33:58,980
Otherwise, I didn't think
I'd get a chance to talk to you.

729
00:33:59,815 --> 00:34:03,084
I don't think I'm the type
to lead conversations...

730
00:34:03,085 --> 00:34:05,186
when I'm with a group of people.

731
00:34:06,455 --> 00:34:07,855
I'm different
when it's just the two of us.

732
00:34:07,856 --> 00:34:09,123
But you're on a roll now.

733
00:34:09,691 --> 00:34:11,792
I'm usually much more talkative.

734
00:34:11,927 --> 00:34:14,629
I actually love chatting and rambling on.

735
00:34:15,531 --> 00:34:17,232
You can do that with me.

736
00:34:17,599 --> 00:34:18,899
Please do.

737
00:34:19,168 --> 00:34:20,034
I already am.

738
00:34:20,435 --> 00:34:21,235
Awesome.

739
00:34:22,404 --> 00:34:24,138
I'm happy no matter
what we're talking about right now.

740
00:34:25,807 --> 00:34:27,274
(Smiling)

741
00:34:27,376 --> 00:34:29,109
I never thought you'd pick me.

742
00:34:29,110 --> 00:34:30,703
I had no idea either.

743
00:34:32,114 --> 00:34:33,448
But I wanted to tell you.

744
00:34:34,049 --> 00:34:35,783
You did? Thank you.

745
00:34:36,084 --> 00:34:37,151
I'm suddenly in a really good mood.

746
00:34:37,352 --> 00:34:39,753
(Chuckling)

747
00:34:39,754 --> 00:34:40,621
I'm happy now.

748
00:34:41,023 --> 00:34:42,290
He's so excited.

749
00:34:43,125 --> 00:34:45,393
Doesn't he look super happy?

750
00:34:45,394 --> 00:34:47,261
He's smiling the whole time.

751
00:34:47,262 --> 00:34:49,430
When a guy says,

752
00:34:49,431 --> 00:34:53,167
"I'm so happy right now," I think
that would feel really nice to hear.

753
00:34:53,168 --> 00:34:55,236
From a woman's perspective,

754
00:34:55,237 --> 00:34:58,206
it's incredibly appreciated
when he's honest about how he's feeling.

755
00:34:58,207 --> 00:34:59,173
True.

756
00:34:59,174 --> 00:35:01,976
Men usually don't express themselves
like that.

757
00:35:01,977 --> 00:35:03,177
- Right.
- They don't often say,

758
00:35:03,178 --> 00:35:05,847
"I'm so happy right now,"
or "I feel great."

759
00:35:05,848 --> 00:35:07,248
We're shy.

760
00:35:07,249 --> 00:35:08,516
That's exactly the charm of a younger man.

761
00:35:09,751 --> 00:35:11,484
(Jin Woo and Ji Hye's First-to-Claim Date)

762
00:35:11,485 --> 00:35:12,802
I'll make sure
you have a great time today.

763
00:35:13,388 --> 00:35:15,422
Yesterday, when we were talking
about each others' first impressions,

764
00:35:15,958 --> 00:35:18,159
you said I seemed like a soft guy
who's pretending to be macho.

765
00:35:18,660 --> 00:35:19,760
- Yes.
- Do you still think that?

766
00:35:20,596 --> 00:35:22,096
Now, I just think you're a very soft guy.

767
00:35:22,397 --> 00:35:23,864
Do people usually call you a macho man?

768
00:35:24,099 --> 00:35:27,168
Me? I think so myself.

769
00:35:27,736 --> 00:35:30,071
(Yourself?)

770
00:35:30,072 --> 00:35:30,930
A self-proclaimed macho man?

771
00:35:31,306 --> 00:35:33,574
"A self-proclaimed?"

772
00:35:35,177 --> 00:35:37,411
I think you're actually very soft.

773
00:35:37,412 --> 00:35:38,279
What makes you think so?

774
00:35:38,580 --> 00:35:41,448
The way you talk and act.

775
00:35:42,084 --> 00:35:43,618
You're really sweet.

776
00:35:44,120 --> 00:35:46,121
Does being sweet make me a soft guy?

777
00:35:46,122 --> 00:35:46,888
Of course.

778
00:35:47,956 --> 00:35:49,506
You're don't seem to act tough
while secretly caring.

779
00:35:49,531 --> 00:35:51,292
You're openly thoughtful.

780
00:35:52,194 --> 00:35:54,328
I actually looked out for you
quite a bit yesterday.

781
00:35:54,329 --> 00:35:56,932
You did. I appreciated that.

782
00:35:56,933 --> 00:35:58,799
So you noticed. Thank you.

783
00:35:59,634 --> 00:36:01,069
(Shy)

784
00:36:01,070 --> 00:36:02,536
Those two look good together.

785
00:36:03,372 --> 00:36:04,706
What was your first impression of me?

786
00:36:05,741 --> 00:36:06,541
It was...

787
00:36:07,943 --> 00:36:08,743
good.

788
00:36:09,244 --> 00:36:10,110
Goodness.

789
00:36:10,111 --> 00:36:11,679
(Well...)

790
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:13,681
Then why didn't you pick me?

791
00:36:13,949 --> 00:36:15,850
- Pick you for what?
- For the First Impression Vote.

792
00:36:16,952 --> 00:36:19,287
(His eyes begin darting around.)

793
00:36:21,823 --> 00:36:24,191
Hold on.
I'm not very good at multitasking.

794
00:36:24,859 --> 00:36:26,827
I keep switching back and forth
between formal and casual speech.

795
00:36:27,163 --> 00:36:28,496
Can I just speak casually from now on?

796
00:36:28,497 --> 00:36:30,131
- Then should we both do it?
- Sure.

797
00:36:30,399 --> 00:36:31,232
Let's just talk casually.

798
00:36:32,067 --> 00:36:32,933
That's a big step.

799
00:36:37,172 --> 00:36:38,839
(Reaching out his hand)

800
00:36:40,008 --> 00:36:41,542
That was very considerate.

801
00:36:43,478 --> 00:36:45,079
I was a bit embarrassed.

802
00:36:45,948 --> 00:36:47,516
(Jin Woo gets flustered
by Ji Hye's compliment.)

803
00:36:47,517 --> 00:36:48,583
That was sweet.

804
00:36:49,485 --> 00:36:52,653
But didn't he hold out his arm
like a robot?

805
00:36:52,654 --> 00:36:53,821
(Whirring)

806
00:36:53,822 --> 00:36:54,722
Like this.

807
00:36:54,858 --> 00:36:56,291
(Laughing)

808
00:36:56,758 --> 00:36:58,792
Yesterday, the question for you was...

809
00:36:58,793 --> 00:37:03,330
what moment would make
your heart race the most.

810
00:37:03,532 --> 00:37:04,465
You said the first date.

811
00:37:04,466 --> 00:37:07,268
That's right.
You have a really good memory.

812
00:37:07,269 --> 00:37:08,135
I remember everything.

813
00:37:08,337 --> 00:37:09,304
You have a good memory.

814
00:37:09,338 --> 00:37:11,372
(The question Ji Hye picked)

815
00:37:11,540 --> 00:37:15,209
"What moment do you think will make
your heart race the most in Yeon House?"

816
00:37:15,210 --> 00:37:15,976
I'm curious.

817
00:37:17,479 --> 00:37:20,081
- The first date.
- Me too.

818
00:37:20,182 --> 00:37:22,517
- It's tomorrow.
- Oh, that's right.

819
00:37:22,684 --> 00:37:24,018
It's tomorrow, right?

820
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:27,454
He remembers every detail,
and now they're on a date together.

821
00:37:27,956 --> 00:37:31,258
You know how I'm wearing
this polka dot outfit today?

822
00:37:31,427 --> 00:37:33,527
I'd already decided...

823
00:37:33,528 --> 00:37:35,597
- that I'd wear this on my first date.
- So you'd planned it.

824
00:37:35,598 --> 00:37:36,464
For the first date?

825
00:37:36,666 --> 00:37:38,532
But then you suddenly showed up wearing
a blue top.

826
00:37:39,434 --> 00:37:41,035
So when you said, "Should we match
our outfits?"

827
00:37:41,036 --> 00:37:43,070
- Right.
- I was shocked.

828
00:37:43,339 --> 00:37:44,872
I thought
that was such a crazy coincidence.

829
00:37:46,108 --> 00:37:47,408
- We were lucky.
- Right.

830
00:37:48,410 --> 00:37:49,977
The timing was perfect.

831
00:37:50,545 --> 00:37:51,411
Maybe it's destiny.

832
00:37:52,180 --> 00:37:53,580
She's quite impatient.

833
00:37:54,049 --> 00:37:56,384
Those two have a comfortable vibe,
but there's some chemistry in the air.

834
00:37:56,385 --> 00:37:58,386
I'm really curious how old you are.

835
00:37:59,221 --> 00:38:00,321
I can't wait to find out.

836
00:38:01,356 --> 00:38:03,924
- Sorry, I forgot to check the navigation.
- It's okay.

837
00:38:03,925 --> 00:38:04,892
Just leave it.

838
00:38:05,394 --> 00:38:06,894
Why are your hands so cold?

839
00:38:06,895 --> 00:38:08,796
- Because of the air conditioner.
- Goodness.

840
00:38:08,797 --> 00:38:10,365
- Are you flirting with me right now?
- Yes, I am.

841
00:38:10,366 --> 00:38:11,711
We're going to get
into an accident like this.

842
00:38:12,567 --> 00:38:13,667
(Giggling)

843
00:38:14,569 --> 00:38:15,736
(Dopey grin)

844
00:38:15,737 --> 00:38:18,572
(Oh, my gosh!)

845
00:38:18,573 --> 00:38:19,440
What's that?

846
00:38:19,441 --> 00:38:21,942
She knows how to keep Jin Woo on his toes.

847
00:38:22,344 --> 00:38:25,246
Jin Woo is completely flustered.

848
00:38:25,247 --> 00:38:26,281
She has him completely flustered.

849
00:38:26,282 --> 00:38:28,849
Why is he freezing up
over something like that?

850
00:38:29,351 --> 00:38:30,985
The longer Jin Woo keeps driving,

851
00:38:30,986 --> 00:38:33,220
the bigger his smile gets.

852
00:38:33,221 --> 00:38:35,122
I think he's drooling too.

853
00:38:36,191 --> 00:38:38,225
From what I saw,

854
00:38:38,226 --> 00:38:39,894
Ji Hye's hand just brushed
against his hand.

855
00:38:39,895 --> 00:38:43,064
Then she noticed how cold it was
and checked again because she was worried.

856
00:38:43,065 --> 00:38:43,964
Right.

857
00:38:44,166 --> 00:38:45,834
But then he said,
"Are you flirting with me right now?"

858
00:38:45,835 --> 00:38:47,635
and Ji Hye played right along with it.

859
00:38:47,836 --> 00:38:49,236
She said, "Yes, I am."

860
00:38:49,638 --> 00:38:52,005
If I were Jin Woo,
I think I would've held her hand.

861
00:38:52,941 --> 00:38:54,975
- Seriously?
- Yes.

862
00:38:55,677 --> 00:38:57,945
- "You started flirting with me first."
- "You started this,"

863
00:38:58,180 --> 00:38:59,413
"so don't pull away now."

864
00:38:59,414 --> 00:39:00,548
I actually agree with him.

865
00:39:00,549 --> 00:39:01,649
You should commit to it.

866
00:39:01,650 --> 00:39:05,619
If Ji Hye suddenly started
caressing my hand,

867
00:39:05,620 --> 00:39:06,887
I would've pulled
the car over immediately.

868
00:39:06,888 --> 00:39:08,422
And what would you do after pulling over?

869
00:39:08,423 --> 00:39:10,524
I'd just pull over right away.

870
00:39:11,793 --> 00:39:13,427
- Are you flirting with me right now?
- Yes, I am.

871
00:39:13,428 --> 00:39:14,930
We're seriously going
to get into an accident.

872
00:39:17,700 --> 00:39:20,334
I liked it.
I don't think there's any reason...

873
00:39:20,865 --> 00:39:23,188
to playfully initiate physical contact
with someone you're not interested in.

874
00:39:23,772 --> 00:39:27,108
I liked that she did it
in a playful way first.

875
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:31,377
(Ji Seung and Si Won set off
on their date.)

876
00:39:31,972 --> 00:39:34,618
How long does it take you to get ready?
When you go out?

877
00:39:34,619 --> 00:39:38,706
I can do my makeup in 11 or 12 minutes.

878
00:39:38,830 --> 00:39:42,376
- Really? Because you do it lightly?
- It only takes that long for the makeup.

879
00:39:42,450 --> 00:39:46,881
But I've been putting in more effort
since I came here. This is the effort.

880
00:39:47,048 --> 00:39:48,549
- You look good.
- Never mind.

881
00:39:48,762 --> 00:39:51,194
It felt like you were saying
I didn't put on much makeup.

882
00:39:52,214 --> 00:39:54,489
Can I ask who you voted for yesterday?

883
00:39:56,230 --> 00:39:57,230
It's a secret.

884
00:39:58,087 --> 00:40:01,295
I think I can tell you mine.

885
00:40:02,330 --> 00:40:04,399
(Nervous)

886
00:40:04,646 --> 00:40:07,301
Then, shall we share
just one thing for now?

887
00:40:07,626 --> 00:40:09,238
- Our first impressions?
- First impressions?

888
00:40:10,852 --> 00:40:12,145
I chose you, Si Won.

889
00:40:13,608 --> 00:40:17,879
(Ji Seung chose Si Won
for the First Impression Vote.)

890
00:40:18,530 --> 00:40:19,817
- Really?
- Yes.

891
00:40:20,803 --> 00:40:23,250
- Did you choose someone else?
- I chose you too, Ji Seung.

892
00:40:24,250 --> 00:40:28,435
They chose each other.
It's always been each other, even now.

893
00:40:28,460 --> 00:40:29,724
(They chose each other on the first day.)

894
00:40:30,424 --> 00:40:31,254
(Relieved)

895
00:40:31,255 --> 00:40:32,255
I thought you chose someone else.

896
00:40:37,731 --> 00:40:40,768
(The two discover that they were
each other's choice.)

897
00:40:44,070 --> 00:40:47,829
- Which season do you like?
- I'm extremely sensitive to the cold.

898
00:40:47,830 --> 00:40:50,611
I lived in Canada for a bit
when I was a kid,

899
00:40:50,644 --> 00:40:53,581
and it was so cold there.

900
00:40:53,582 --> 00:40:55,849
Whenever it gets cold,
it just brings back those memories.

901
00:40:56,448 --> 00:41:00,071
You know how guys feel about shoveling
snow in the military, right?

902
00:41:00,090 --> 00:41:04,025
I feel that way about the cold.

903
00:41:04,937 --> 00:41:10,336
I actually like summer. I like being able
to go for walks at night.

904
00:41:10,656 --> 00:41:13,567
The summer night air has a great vibe.

905
00:41:13,668 --> 00:41:16,682
- So, I prefer summer over winter.
- Really?

906
00:41:18,428 --> 00:41:20,295
- Let's go for a walk together sometime.
- Sure.

907
00:41:23,467 --> 00:41:25,847
(They make their first promise.)

908
00:41:25,859 --> 00:41:27,682
(Grinning)

909
00:41:28,899 --> 00:41:31,052
- Look, the flowers are blooming.
- There is a cherry blossom street.

910
00:41:31,592 --> 00:41:32,753
The road is so pretty.

911
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:34,922
(Glancing)

912
00:41:35,898 --> 00:41:36,898
Shall we go slower?

913
00:41:37,138 --> 00:41:38,178
(Grinning)

914
00:41:38,179 --> 00:41:39,179
Shall we go slower?

915
00:41:40,524 --> 00:41:44,532
(Ji Seung smiles
at Si Won's thoughtful gesture.)

916
00:41:45,051 --> 00:41:46,323
(They arrive at the date spot.)

917
00:41:46,324 --> 00:41:47,435
It's pretty, right?

918
00:41:48,189 --> 00:41:49,670
- Right. It's so pretty here.
- Right.

919
00:41:49,703 --> 00:41:52,273
- It's like a hidden cafe.
- Right.

920
00:41:54,122 --> 00:41:57,414
This is the crème brûlée.
You said you wanted to try the salt bread.

921
00:41:58,308 --> 00:42:00,575
- It looks good.
- I'll cut it for you.

922
00:42:00,662 --> 00:42:02,227
- In half.
- Thank you.

923
00:42:05,794 --> 00:42:07,155
The table is shaking so much.

924
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:09,180
Should I hold it for you?

925
00:42:10,618 --> 00:42:11,992
I should hold this.

926
00:42:12,994 --> 00:42:14,295
(Smiling)

927
00:42:14,498 --> 00:42:16,697
- I really like how easygoing you are.
- Really?

928
00:42:18,238 --> 00:42:19,700
I feel like I'm acting
too much like a warrior.

929
00:42:21,469 --> 00:42:22,991
(Something is off.)

930
00:42:23,143 --> 00:42:28,242
Aren't you supposed to cut
this along the grain? Isn't it like this?

931
00:42:30,996 --> 00:42:34,048
- I've never cut a salt bread.
- Just rip it apart with your hands.

932
00:42:34,049 --> 00:42:35,049
Should I?

933
00:42:39,133 --> 00:42:41,021
Right now, Ji Seung thinks
Si Won is so cute.

934
00:42:41,586 --> 00:42:43,773
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

935
00:42:44,191 --> 00:42:47,628
(Taking a bite)

936
00:42:51,615 --> 00:42:54,101
- It's good.
- It's good?

937
00:42:55,568 --> 00:42:57,420
- These two are...
- They look good together.

938
00:42:57,547 --> 00:42:58,834
going smoothly.

939
00:42:59,841 --> 00:43:03,513
When you're dating someone,
are you usually the type to take the lead?

940
00:43:04,040 --> 00:43:07,014
Take the lead? I don't really think
I take the lead.

941
00:43:07,326 --> 00:43:10,084
When I start a relationship,

942
00:43:10,505 --> 00:43:13,955
I am not the type to be
very proactive first. What about you?

943
00:43:14,205 --> 00:43:15,723
When starting a relationship?

944
00:43:15,778 --> 00:43:19,291
Usually, men tend to be
a bit more proactive.

945
00:43:19,324 --> 00:43:20,561
That's more likely.

946
00:43:21,357 --> 00:43:26,480
For me, once I'm sure about my feelings,
I think I just go all in.

947
00:43:26,501 --> 00:43:28,469
(Once I'm sure about my feelings,
I think I just go all in.)

948
00:43:28,655 --> 00:43:32,573
- Are you good at playing hard to get?
- Do you think I would be?

949
00:43:34,282 --> 00:43:36,477
- Maybe a little bit?
- Really?

950
00:43:36,921 --> 00:43:38,479
- Or do you not at all?
- That's a first.

951
00:43:39,174 --> 00:43:41,482
I have never played hard to get before.

952
00:43:42,154 --> 00:43:46,426
It's just that my pace is a bit slow.

953
00:43:47,188 --> 00:43:48,446
(Input complete)

954
00:43:48,447 --> 00:43:49,620
Si Won is so handsome.

955
00:43:49,766 --> 00:43:52,042
- What?
- What's wrong?

956
00:43:52,336 --> 00:43:54,169
I spilled quite a lot of food.

957
00:43:54,836 --> 00:43:58,095
What should I do?
There is even some blueberry on it.

958
00:43:58,595 --> 00:44:01,595
Should I go get you some wet wipes?
I'll go and get them.

959
00:44:03,527 --> 00:44:04,667
Thank you.

960
00:44:04,668 --> 00:44:06,440
(Si Won moves immediately
to help Ji Seung.)

961
00:44:06,706 --> 00:44:09,452
Younger men are always
very quick to take action.

962
00:44:10,347 --> 00:44:11,846
I was basically a servant.

963
00:44:11,979 --> 00:44:15,315
When I used to date an older woman,
I'd bow like this when I got home.

964
00:44:15,825 --> 00:44:16,825
I'm home.

965
00:44:20,219 --> 00:44:21,623
- It's coming off.
- It is?

966
00:44:22,051 --> 00:44:23,858
- I think it got on this part as well.
- Where?

967
00:44:25,284 --> 00:44:27,094
Really? Come on.

968
00:44:27,516 --> 00:44:28,829
How did you get so much on that?

969
00:44:29,957 --> 00:44:31,399
I think I need a bib.

970
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:32,400
(A bib?)

971
00:44:32,867 --> 00:44:34,135
(Looking around)

972
00:44:34,242 --> 00:44:36,882
- Did you seriously look for an apron?
- If they had anything at all.

973
00:44:36,935 --> 00:44:38,714
No, it's fine.

974
00:44:39,228 --> 00:44:41,642
I think he was just putting
on his sweet guy persona.

975
00:44:42,061 --> 00:44:44,278
Looking for an apron
at a cafe is too forced.

976
00:44:45,387 --> 00:44:47,915
- How are you feeling right now?
- Me? I'm doing pretty well.

977
00:44:48,849 --> 00:44:51,151
- Things are a bit hectic, though.
- Of course.

978
00:44:51,706 --> 00:44:54,055
- I also feel a bit hectic right now.
- What's making you feel like that?

979
00:44:54,526 --> 00:44:56,929
First of all, I think I'm trying to figure
out everyone's personality bit by bit.

980
00:44:57,164 --> 00:44:59,560
- Really?
- That includes the other men as well.

981
00:44:59,665 --> 00:45:01,261
Right.

982
00:45:01,877 --> 00:45:06,397
Aside from you, there's no one
else I've really gotten to know here.

983
00:45:07,363 --> 00:45:09,457
Did you get to know anyone else?
No, right?

984
00:45:09,903 --> 00:45:11,772
Other women? I haven't either.

985
00:45:12,006 --> 00:45:12,823
(Relieved)

986
00:45:12,848 --> 00:45:16,787
I was just asking. I wondered if you might
have talked to anyone else in passing.

987
00:45:16,848 --> 00:45:19,421
- She's checking.
- She is definitely checking, right?

988
00:45:19,446 --> 00:45:21,072
She's testing him, right?

989
00:45:21,401 --> 00:45:22,401
Totally.

990
00:45:22,402 --> 00:45:23,751
(She's totally testing the waters.)

991
00:45:23,827 --> 00:45:26,763
I didn't really talk much yesterday.

992
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:29,323
That's probably why people said
I seemed quiet.

993
00:45:31,383 --> 00:45:34,116
- I wonder if I should try talking more.
- Really?

994
00:45:35,849 --> 00:45:38,089
- I guess I should speak up a bit more.
- Like calling people out?

995
00:45:38,169 --> 00:45:40,001
I'm not quite sure about that.

996
00:45:40,606 --> 00:45:43,104
- Calling them out to talk.
- Are you planning to go that far?

997
00:45:43,546 --> 00:45:46,007
I'm not really the type of person
who can do that.

998
00:45:46,502 --> 00:45:48,376
The emotional tug-of-war
between them is no joke.

999
00:45:48,755 --> 00:45:53,547
I feel like the time is too short
to fully get to know even just one person.

1000
00:45:56,383 --> 00:45:58,552
(Thinking)

1001
00:45:58,606 --> 00:46:02,759
What did you say your ideal type was
when we were talking about it yesterday?

1002
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:04,132
I remember one thing.

1003
00:46:04,535 --> 00:46:06,197
You said a boring person is
better than a dopamine rush.

1004
00:46:06,753 --> 00:46:08,295
- A stable, boring person.
- Right, a stable person.

1005
00:46:08,725 --> 00:46:10,898
Naturally,

1006
00:46:11,304 --> 00:46:14,168
a dopamine rush is a part of love,
but I don't think that defines love.

1007
00:46:14,584 --> 00:46:19,410
Anyone can feel
that initial fluttering excitement,

1008
00:46:19,516 --> 00:46:22,576
but that feeling needs to last,
and it usually doesn't.

1009
00:46:23,109 --> 00:46:25,268
That's true. You can't keep
that excitement going for a lifetime.

1010
00:46:25,292 --> 00:46:26,460
For me,

1011
00:46:28,795 --> 00:46:33,287
it feels more like love grows
and becomes stronger over time,

1012
00:46:33,827 --> 00:46:38,046
after I show everything to the person...

1013
00:46:38,047 --> 00:46:42,396
and we build a very deep mutual trust.

1014
00:46:42,726 --> 00:46:44,145
That shows her maturity and experience.

1015
00:46:44,218 --> 00:46:46,533
So, it's like going from zero
to a hundred for you? Usually?

1016
00:46:46,631 --> 00:46:48,435
Right. But my feelings never drop
once they reach a hundred.

1017
00:46:48,658 --> 00:46:51,005
- Really?
- I never experienced a relationship rut.

1018
00:46:51,445 --> 00:46:53,964
- Never?
- Never.

1019
00:46:55,484 --> 00:46:58,446
- That's actually quite surprising.
- I don't have those flat periods,

1020
00:46:58,557 --> 00:47:00,557
even if I date someone for a long time.

1021
00:47:02,255 --> 00:47:04,429
I feel like you would be...

1022
00:47:05,956 --> 00:47:07,755
a wonderful girlfriend
when you're in a relationship.

1023
00:47:08,213 --> 00:47:10,033
I think I'm actually quite good
to my boyfriends.

1024
00:47:11,239 --> 00:47:12,593
You're quite good?

1025
00:47:12,741 --> 00:47:15,922
I find it comfortable
to accommodate my partner.

1026
00:47:16,864 --> 00:47:20,167
I think I try to talk a lot
to accommodate each other.

1027
00:47:21,134 --> 00:47:22,830
I feel like you would be
a great boyfriend as well.

1028
00:47:25,907 --> 00:47:27,007
They look so good together.

1029
00:47:28,287 --> 00:47:31,973
Should I say he felt quite manly?
He had that kind of leadership.

1030
00:47:32,113 --> 00:47:35,616
When I first meet someone
and get close to them,

1031
00:47:35,811 --> 00:47:38,986
it makes me feel more comfortable
if they lead the way like this.

1032
00:47:39,418 --> 00:47:41,555
It allows me to show my true colors...

1033
00:47:42,122 --> 00:47:45,292
and approach them more easily.

1034
00:47:45,726 --> 00:47:48,395
I think that's what I found attractive
about him.

1035
00:47:48,396 --> 00:47:49,563
(She slowly gets to know his charms.)

1036
00:47:49,756 --> 00:47:53,066
I think the two of them have
very similar personalities.

1037
00:47:53,955 --> 00:47:56,302
Neither of them has any desire
to make the conversation interesting.

1038
00:47:57,410 --> 00:48:00,274
Do you know what I mean?
From a third-person perspective,

1039
00:48:00,394 --> 00:48:03,061
there was absolutely nothing funny
about their conversation.

1040
00:48:03,420 --> 00:48:06,403
Yet, the two of them are laughing
over something as simple as crème brûlée.

1041
00:48:06,983 --> 00:48:10,650
- They just share a calm emotional vibe.
- I think that calm vibe fits them.

1042
00:48:10,878 --> 00:48:12,094
- They match very well.
- Right.

1043
00:48:12,114 --> 00:48:14,430
Their emotional temperaments are similar,

1044
00:48:14,929 --> 00:48:16,457
and the pace of their interaction is
also similar.

1045
00:48:16,895 --> 00:48:19,026
- They are a perfect match.
- Right.

1046
00:48:21,074 --> 00:48:24,331
(Yu Jin and Jun Han arrive
at their date spot.)

1047
00:48:24,356 --> 00:48:25,689
Where is that?

1048
00:48:29,566 --> 00:48:30,566
Left side or right?

1049
00:48:31,253 --> 00:48:34,475
(Jun Han thoughtfully considers
where she sits.)

1050
00:48:36,176 --> 00:48:38,218
(Looking around)

1051
00:48:38,219 --> 00:48:39,846
Oh, it's hot. This is hot. Be careful.

1052
00:48:40,414 --> 00:48:42,082
Be careful.

1053
00:48:42,163 --> 00:48:44,818
The view is so nice.

1054
00:48:49,103 --> 00:48:50,743
It's so pretty.

1055
00:48:53,060 --> 00:48:54,461
(Glancing)

1056
00:48:54,462 --> 00:48:55,462
I got it.

1057
00:48:56,302 --> 00:48:58,302
You know what?

1058
00:48:58,976 --> 00:49:00,043
On a date,

1059
00:49:01,143 --> 00:49:02,676
a princess shouldn't have to do anything.

1060
00:49:02,676 --> 00:49:04,276
(Embarrassed)

1061
00:49:04,276 --> 00:49:05,909
This is so embarrassing.
I should go order something.

1062
00:49:05,909 --> 00:49:07,276
I'll be right back.

1063
00:49:07,276 --> 00:49:08,543
That's insane!

1064
00:49:08,543 --> 00:49:12,376
(Jun Han quickly leaves the table
after his shocking comment.)

1065
00:49:12,543 --> 00:49:15,343
- Oh, boy.
- I have a feeling.

1066
00:49:15,343 --> 00:49:18,143
Jun Han said he'd dated
a lot of older women, right?

1067
00:49:18,143 --> 00:49:20,476
I think I know exactly what kind
of older women he's dated.

1068
00:49:20,709 --> 00:49:22,943
I can totally picture the type.

1069
00:49:22,943 --> 00:49:26,843
Even as a woman,
being called a princess is...

1070
00:49:26,843 --> 00:49:27,943
so cringey.

1071
00:49:27,943 --> 00:49:29,393
(His cuteness leaves
Princess Hye Jin flustered.)

1072
00:49:30,376 --> 00:49:33,509
(Looking away)

1073
00:49:34,443 --> 00:49:35,943
(Laughing)

1074
00:49:36,076 --> 00:49:37,809
Your ears turned red. Did you know?

1075
00:49:38,076 --> 00:49:38,909
- My ears?
- Yes.

1076
00:49:38,909 --> 00:49:40,743
- It's because of the sunlight.
- Really?

1077
00:49:40,743 --> 00:49:42,009
Only your ears?

1078
00:49:42,409 --> 00:49:43,243
(Touching)

1079
00:49:43,243 --> 00:49:45,309
- It was really embarrassing.
- I know.

1080
00:49:45,309 --> 00:49:46,209
He's cute.

1081
00:49:46,209 --> 00:49:47,809
Here we go!

1082
00:49:47,809 --> 00:49:50,043
(Finding him adorable)

1083
00:49:50,068 --> 00:49:53,334
- Thank you.
- Here's your food and drinks.

1084
00:49:53,943 --> 00:49:55,743
(Showing his thoughtful side
by refilling her water)

1085
00:49:55,743 --> 00:49:57,002
- Would you like some water?
- Yes, please.

1086
00:49:58,443 --> 00:49:59,543
Thank you.

1087
00:50:01,709 --> 00:50:04,043
- Enjoy your meal.
- Enjoy.

1088
00:50:06,343 --> 00:50:07,176
Do you drink?

1089
00:50:07,409 --> 00:50:08,776
Occasionally, I do.

1090
00:50:08,776 --> 00:50:11,409
- I love pairing drinks with good food.
- Oh, I like that too.

1091
00:50:11,409 --> 00:50:13,343
You know how there are people...

1092
00:50:14,143 --> 00:50:17,476
who feel like they have to finish
an entire bottle of soju every day?

1093
00:50:17,476 --> 00:50:19,909
I don't understand those people.

1094
00:50:19,909 --> 00:50:21,876
But having a glass of whiskey?

1095
00:50:21,876 --> 00:50:23,809
That's perfectly fine.

1096
00:50:24,976 --> 00:50:26,176
What if your girlfriend...

1097
00:50:26,176 --> 00:50:28,409
has to drink every day because of work?

1098
00:50:30,076 --> 00:50:31,376
I'd completely understand.

1099
00:50:31,643 --> 00:50:33,043
- Because it's her job.
- Because it's work?

1100
00:50:33,043 --> 00:50:35,176
She can even meet guys because of work.

1101
00:50:35,176 --> 00:50:36,243
Really?

1102
00:50:36,543 --> 00:50:38,476
Under one condition.

1103
00:50:39,192 --> 00:50:40,379
She has to let me pick her up afterward.

1104
00:50:41,243 --> 00:50:42,509
She can drink and can hang out.

1105
00:50:42,509 --> 00:50:45,909
As long as she has nothing to hide
when I come to get her,

1106
00:50:45,909 --> 00:50:48,643
she can do whatever she wants.

1107
00:50:48,643 --> 00:50:50,109
That sounds reasonable.

1108
00:50:50,109 --> 00:50:50,976
That's how I see it.

1109
00:50:51,443 --> 00:50:52,802
What about you?
If the situation were reversed?

1110
00:50:54,076 --> 00:50:56,243
Me too. I'm exactly the same.

1111
00:50:56,243 --> 00:50:57,509
- So you're okay with that?
- Yes.

1112
00:50:58,776 --> 00:51:00,476
Let's say my boyfriend wants to go...

1113
00:51:00,476 --> 00:51:02,609
to a night, I mean, a club.

1114
00:51:02,609 --> 00:51:04,443
She said "nightclub!"

1115
00:51:04,443 --> 00:51:06,242
- It means she's older than me!
- What's wrong with nightclubs?

1116
00:51:06,267 --> 00:51:07,909
- That's even older than me!
- Come on.

1117
00:51:07,909 --> 00:51:10,809
Maybe her favorite club was
literally called "Night."

1118
00:51:10,809 --> 00:51:12,676
All right.

1119
00:51:12,843 --> 00:51:14,676
Let's say my boyfriend wants to go...

1120
00:51:14,676 --> 00:51:16,643
to a night, I mean, a club.

1121
00:51:16,876 --> 00:51:18,143
I'd still be okay with it.

1122
00:51:18,843 --> 00:51:20,176
Because...

1123
00:51:21,643 --> 00:51:23,876
I feel the same way.
"If you have nothing to hide, it's fine."

1124
00:51:24,943 --> 00:51:27,309
And if he's capable of cheating on me
in that situation,

1125
00:51:27,309 --> 00:51:28,543
then he wasn't the right person anyway.

1126
00:51:28,543 --> 00:51:30,943
- I'd almost be grateful...
- Grateful?

1127
00:51:30,943 --> 00:51:32,509
for him leaving me. That's my mindset.

1128
00:51:32,509 --> 00:51:36,276
- Before things go too far?
- Exactly.

1129
00:51:36,276 --> 00:51:39,409
That's why I don't really mind
what he does.

1130
00:51:41,476 --> 00:51:43,476
I think we have a lot in common.

1131
00:51:43,476 --> 00:51:44,876
I know. Interesting.

1132
00:51:45,076 --> 00:51:47,809
(Nodding)

1133
00:51:48,076 --> 00:51:50,743
Everything else aside,
I find that really interesting.

1134
00:51:50,743 --> 00:51:51,843
Me too.

1135
00:51:52,409 --> 00:51:55,476
I've never met someone
who thinks so similarly to me.

1136
00:51:57,943 --> 00:52:00,476
Do you usually take your time
before making things official?

1137
00:52:00,976 --> 00:52:02,576
Honestly, based on my past experiences,

1138
00:52:02,576 --> 00:52:04,543
I've always known right away.

1139
00:52:04,543 --> 00:52:05,409
- You got a feeling?
- Yes.

1140
00:52:05,409 --> 00:52:08,509
- I knew I'd end up dating them.
- Really?

1141
00:52:08,509 --> 00:52:09,276
Yes.

1142
00:52:09,709 --> 00:52:10,776
Do you feel that with anyone here?

1143
00:52:12,409 --> 00:52:13,276
That's a secret.

1144
00:52:18,143 --> 00:52:19,376
I see.

1145
00:52:19,376 --> 00:52:21,309
Does that mean it's not him?

1146
00:52:21,309 --> 00:52:22,909
No. It could be him.

1147
00:52:23,243 --> 00:52:25,709
But out of everyone...

1148
00:52:25,709 --> 00:52:27,476
I've talked to so far,

1149
00:52:27,476 --> 00:52:29,343
the person I've felt...

1150
00:52:29,343 --> 00:52:33,809
the strongest connection with is...

1151
00:52:33,809 --> 00:52:35,543
(Nervous)

1152
00:52:36,276 --> 00:52:38,543
You, Jun Han.

1153
00:52:41,176 --> 00:52:42,543
She just told him it was him?

1154
00:52:42,776 --> 00:52:45,009
You, Jun Han.

1155
00:52:45,643 --> 00:52:46,576
Thank you.

1156
00:52:47,109 --> 00:52:48,343
Should we order more food?

1157
00:52:48,343 --> 00:52:49,943
(Joking)

1158
00:52:53,643 --> 00:52:55,143
Thank you. I love hearing that.

1159
00:52:55,143 --> 00:52:55,976
Okay.

1160
00:52:56,543 --> 00:52:58,340
Let's come back and see
the cherry blossoms together next year.

1161
00:52:59,643 --> 00:53:03,409
That'd be nice.
That would become such a great memory.

1162
00:53:05,243 --> 00:53:06,776
It was a really nice date.
I found him adorable.

1163
00:53:07,376 --> 00:53:08,776
I liked him more than I expected.

1164
00:53:08,776 --> 00:53:11,443
He has a surprisingly serious side too.

1165
00:53:12,309 --> 00:53:15,143
I think if he had a girlfriend, he'd be...

1166
00:53:16,243 --> 00:53:17,443
incredibly kind,

1167
00:53:17,443 --> 00:53:19,843
completely devoted,

1168
00:53:19,843 --> 00:53:21,576
and makes her very happy.

1169
00:53:23,676 --> 00:53:25,188
- Would you like me to take your picture?
- A photo?

1170
00:53:25,443 --> 00:53:26,509
Let's take one together.

1171
00:53:27,109 --> 00:53:27,976
Should we sit down?

1172
00:53:28,409 --> 00:53:29,243
Or stand up?

1173
00:53:30,209 --> 00:53:32,443
- Let's show how similar our outfits are.
- Great idea.

1174
00:53:32,809 --> 00:53:33,976
Could you lower the camera a little?

1175
00:53:33,976 --> 00:53:37,009
(Playful)

1176
00:53:38,009 --> 00:53:38,976
That's a great photo.

1177
00:53:39,376 --> 00:53:40,743
They look good together.

1178
00:53:40,976 --> 00:53:41,876
They really do.

1179
00:53:43,843 --> 00:53:45,309
What did you think of their date?

1180
00:53:46,109 --> 00:53:50,843
- It's Yu Jin's first time...
- I know.

1181
00:53:50,843 --> 00:53:52,176
dating a younger man.

1182
00:53:52,176 --> 00:53:55,143
If that's the case,
Jun Han feels like the right fit for her.

1183
00:53:55,143 --> 00:53:57,909
I think Yu Jin needs someone
as attentive as him.

1184
00:53:57,909 --> 00:53:59,943
So far, he seems great.

1185
00:53:59,943 --> 00:54:01,709
If she had to choose someone here,

1186
00:54:01,709 --> 00:54:04,276
I think Jun Han would be
the best choice too.

1187
00:54:04,276 --> 00:54:06,876
There could be some unexpected chemistry
between them.

1188
00:54:07,143 --> 00:54:08,943
It wasn't bad, right?

1189
00:54:08,943 --> 00:54:10,276
It was perfect.

1190
00:54:10,276 --> 00:54:11,143
(Ju Hee and Yun So arrive.)

1191
00:54:13,209 --> 00:54:14,343
Where would you like to sit?

1192
00:54:14,976 --> 00:54:15,843
The right side or the left?

1193
00:54:16,276 --> 00:54:18,176
I'll sit over there.

1194
00:54:20,076 --> 00:54:23,109
He's considerate in every little way.

1195
00:54:23,109 --> 00:54:25,243
His manners come so naturally.

1196
00:54:25,576 --> 00:54:26,576
(Looking around)

1197
00:54:26,576 --> 00:54:28,876
- This place is beautiful.
- It is.

1198
00:54:30,109 --> 00:54:32,109
(Staring)

1199
00:54:33,676 --> 00:54:36,176
When I saw her profile, I thought
she was incredibly beautiful.

1200
00:54:36,176 --> 00:54:37,043
Oh, my.

1201
00:54:37,609 --> 00:54:38,976
It's been a long time...

1202
00:54:40,309 --> 00:54:41,076
since I felt this way.

1203
00:54:41,076 --> 00:54:43,609
That's why I was so intrigued.

1204
00:54:43,609 --> 00:54:44,609
Oh, my goodness.

1205
00:54:45,109 --> 00:54:48,709
One of the biggest reasons
I chose you was...

1206
00:54:48,709 --> 00:54:50,543
because I felt like we had similar vibes.

1207
00:54:50,543 --> 00:54:52,509
Even though we barely talked.

1208
00:54:52,509 --> 00:54:54,776
Even so, I felt a strong sense
of similarity with you.

1209
00:54:55,009 --> 00:54:59,409
Of course,
you're also the most beautiful physically.

1210
00:55:00,209 --> 00:55:01,743
(Shy)

1211
00:55:03,876 --> 00:55:05,243
How many Love QRs
did you receive last night?

1212
00:55:05,643 --> 00:55:06,643
One.

1213
00:55:06,643 --> 00:55:07,643
- Really?
- Yes.

1214
00:55:09,009 --> 00:55:09,909
Why only one?

1215
00:55:10,476 --> 00:55:11,443
How many did you get?

1216
00:55:12,043 --> 00:55:12,909
- Me?
- Yes.

1217
00:55:13,743 --> 00:55:14,976
- Do you really want to know?
- Yes.

1218
00:55:17,043 --> 00:55:18,169
Should I be worried about competition?

1219
00:55:19,209 --> 00:55:20,143
I got three.

1220
00:55:20,443 --> 00:55:21,476
- Really?
- Yes.

1221
00:55:21,476 --> 00:55:22,409
(Surprised)

1222
00:55:24,509 --> 00:55:26,643
You're the most popular.

1223
00:55:27,943 --> 00:55:29,343
I had no idea.

1224
00:55:29,343 --> 00:55:30,676
I didn't expect to get three either.

1225
00:55:32,109 --> 00:55:35,043
"Even though three people chose me,
I still chose you."

1226
00:55:35,943 --> 00:55:38,243
Yun So showing off
about getting three QRs is...

1227
00:55:38,243 --> 00:55:39,609
- kind of cute too.
- Yes.

1228
00:55:39,609 --> 00:55:40,943
She probably finds that adorable.

1229
00:55:41,476 --> 00:55:42,809
It was so unexpected.

1230
00:55:44,476 --> 00:55:45,943
I was one of the three.

1231
00:55:46,476 --> 00:55:47,276
I know.

1232
00:55:48,076 --> 00:55:49,243
That's why I was so happy.

1233
00:55:49,476 --> 00:55:52,209
If you weren't,
I wouldn't be nearly as happy.

1234
00:55:52,209 --> 00:55:53,443
I'm glad you were.

1235
00:55:53,443 --> 00:55:56,376
(They confirm that their feelings haven't
changed since Day One.)

1236
00:55:57,443 --> 00:56:00,576
- And last night, Jin Woo?
- Yes.

1237
00:56:00,576 --> 00:56:02,609
He asked you to talk in the Talk Room.

1238
00:56:04,243 --> 00:56:05,243
I didn't feel great about that.

1239
00:56:07,343 --> 00:56:08,309
Oh, my.

1240
00:56:09,543 --> 00:56:10,876
I wanted to ask you out too.

1241
00:56:13,343 --> 00:56:14,443
I had no idea.

1242
00:56:15,109 --> 00:56:17,443
I know I haven't given you many signals.

1243
00:56:18,309 --> 00:56:21,976
But if I ever got the chance to tell you
in person, I wanted to say it.

1244
00:56:24,709 --> 00:56:25,743
That was fast.

1245
00:56:25,743 --> 00:56:26,776
He's good.

1246
00:56:26,776 --> 00:56:28,009
He's really quick.

1247
00:56:28,576 --> 00:56:29,643
But honestly...

1248
00:56:29,976 --> 00:56:34,809
Ever since they got in the car,
all he's done is tell her he likes her.

1249
00:56:34,809 --> 00:56:36,443
"I like you."

1250
00:56:36,443 --> 00:56:37,776
"I got three QRs, but I still like you."

1251
00:56:37,776 --> 00:56:39,409
"I hated seeing you leave with Jin Woo."

1252
00:56:39,409 --> 00:56:40,309
"I like you."

1253
00:56:40,309 --> 00:56:41,309
- Constantly.
- Right.

1254
00:56:42,076 --> 00:56:42,876
Is that okay?

1255
00:56:43,576 --> 00:56:44,576
- I'd love it.
- Really?

1256
00:56:44,576 --> 00:56:50,376
The thing is, Ju Hee feels
exactly the same way.

1257
00:56:50,376 --> 00:56:52,376
That means they're really clicking.

1258
00:56:52,376 --> 00:56:53,509
They're completely on the same page.

1259
00:56:54,376 --> 00:56:57,009
What did you talk about
with Jin Woo last night?

1260
00:57:00,243 --> 00:57:03,476
Honestly, he mostly asked questions,
and I mostly answered.

1261
00:57:03,476 --> 00:57:05,676
It didn't feel like much
of a conversation.

1262
00:57:06,943 --> 00:57:11,876
Pretty much the same topics
everyone talked about together?

1263
00:57:12,276 --> 00:57:16,709
Because of that, I naturally assumed
Jin Woo would choose you again,

1264
00:57:17,209 --> 00:57:20,343
either yesterday or today.

1265
00:57:20,343 --> 00:57:22,543
But in the end,
I was the only one who chose you.

1266
00:57:24,276 --> 00:57:27,476
Maybe there are other people
he's more curious about.

1267
00:57:27,476 --> 00:57:28,509
That could be true.

1268
00:57:28,809 --> 00:57:30,143
She's right.

1269
00:57:30,143 --> 00:57:33,043
Do you have someone you're curious about?

1270
00:57:33,043 --> 00:57:33,876
- Sorry?
- Do you?

1271
00:57:33,876 --> 00:57:34,943
- Me?
- Yes.

1272
00:57:36,843 --> 00:57:37,909
I did.

1273
00:57:37,909 --> 00:57:38,843
"I did?"

1274
00:57:38,843 --> 00:57:40,243
- Someone you're curious about?
- Yes.

1275
00:57:41,576 --> 00:57:43,843
Well, I'm talking to him right now, so...

1276
00:57:43,843 --> 00:57:46,009
Come on.

1277
00:57:46,009 --> 00:57:47,843
That's a move.

1278
00:57:48,043 --> 00:57:49,643
She's so proactive.

1279
00:57:50,009 --> 00:57:52,409
I'm talking to him right now, so...

1280
00:57:52,409 --> 00:57:54,409
(Shy)

1281
00:57:54,409 --> 00:57:55,509
- Me?
- Yes.

1282
00:57:55,509 --> 00:57:56,443
Besides me.

1283
00:57:58,543 --> 00:57:59,409
Well...

1284
00:58:00,709 --> 00:58:02,276
(Flustered)

1285
00:58:08,309 --> 00:58:09,276
Jun Han?

1286
00:58:10,609 --> 00:58:11,776
Jun Han...

1287
00:58:14,076 --> 00:58:15,609
He seems fun.

1288
00:58:15,609 --> 00:58:17,309
(The other person Ju Hee is
curious about is Jun Han.)

1289
00:58:22,909 --> 00:58:23,809
Do you have someone?

1290
00:58:24,176 --> 00:58:25,143
- Me?
- Yes.

1291
00:58:25,609 --> 00:58:27,109
I'm not really good at multitasking.

1292
00:58:28,616 --> 00:58:29,543
So...

1293
00:58:30,343 --> 00:58:32,276
I don't have anyone else.

1294
00:58:34,976 --> 00:58:36,043
Really?

1295
00:58:37,543 --> 00:58:38,876
Wait.

1296
00:58:42,215 --> 00:58:44,076
That's actually really sweet.

1297
00:58:44,076 --> 00:58:44,909
Me?

1298
00:58:45,643 --> 00:58:46,443
No.

1299
00:58:47,376 --> 00:58:49,043
Honestly, it bothered me a little.

1300
00:58:49,043 --> 00:58:52,943
I think I wanted her attention
to be focused only on me.

1301
00:58:52,943 --> 00:58:55,509
I tried my best
not to show my disappointment...

1302
00:58:55,509 --> 00:58:57,476
or let it affect my behavior.

1303
00:58:57,476 --> 00:58:58,903
I was being honest.

1304
00:58:59,750 --> 00:59:00,950
It's just the first day.

1305
00:59:00,951 --> 00:59:03,453
You can't go all in on one person.

1306
00:59:03,454 --> 00:59:04,587
Some people are like him,

1307
00:59:05,189 --> 00:59:06,656
some are not.

1308
00:59:07,858 --> 00:59:12,762
(The atmosphere is
a little different now.)

1309
00:59:13,330 --> 00:59:14,764
So next time,

1310
00:59:16,200 --> 00:59:19,068
if you had a chance to go on a date
with either me or Jun Han,

1311
00:59:19,770 --> 00:59:20,770
who would you choose?

1312
00:59:20,871 --> 00:59:21,971
Yun So is anxious.

1313
00:59:24,308 --> 00:59:25,441
I'd choose you.

1314
00:59:27,811 --> 00:59:28,744
Really?

1315
00:59:29,446 --> 00:59:30,279
Can I trust you?

1316
00:59:34,118 --> 00:59:35,018
Okay.

1317
00:59:35,853 --> 00:59:37,286
He's indeed a younger man.

1318
00:59:37,287 --> 00:59:38,955
- He really is.
- He keeps asking for reassurance.

1319
00:59:41,959 --> 00:59:43,493
What would you like me to call you?

1320
00:59:43,861 --> 00:59:44,994
- Call me?
- Yes.

1321
00:59:47,819 --> 00:59:51,066
I want to call you
whatever you're comfortable with.

1322
00:59:52,436 --> 00:59:54,337
Shall we drop the honorifics?

1323
00:59:54,772 --> 00:59:55,605
Okay.

1324
00:59:56,206 --> 00:59:57,072
I'd like that.

1325
00:59:58,142 --> 01:00:00,610
(Awkward)

1326
01:00:03,814 --> 01:00:06,449
(Smiling)

1327
01:00:07,317 --> 01:00:08,217
What?

1328
01:00:13,757 --> 01:00:16,392
I imagined both a good and a bad scenario.

1329
01:00:21,065 --> 01:00:23,233
What scenarios?

1330
01:00:23,234 --> 01:00:25,368
The good one is that we stay
happy together until the end.

1331
01:00:27,404 --> 01:00:29,972
The bad one is
that you suddenly disappear.

1332
01:00:31,308 --> 01:00:32,675
Suddenly at the end.

1333
01:00:35,512 --> 01:00:36,812
You could disappear too.

1334
01:00:38,348 --> 01:00:39,815
Right. That's possible.

1335
01:00:40,217 --> 01:00:41,918
But for now,
I don't plan on doing that at all,

1336
01:00:42,419 --> 01:00:43,319
so I didn't think about that.

1337
01:00:55,599 --> 01:00:57,467
So, if you could go on a date
with someone else,

1338
01:00:57,468 --> 01:01:00,369
Jun Han would be your second choice,
right?

1339
01:01:01,405 --> 01:01:02,472
Stop it, man.

1340
01:01:02,606 --> 01:01:03,940
(Laughing out loud)

1341
01:01:03,941 --> 01:01:06,343
Please stop. You shouldn't do that.

1342
01:01:06,344 --> 01:01:08,044
This is not a health checkup.

1343
01:01:08,445 --> 01:01:11,313
Looking back, I was like Yun So.

1344
01:01:11,383 --> 01:01:13,416
I wanted to keep showing...

1345
01:01:13,417 --> 01:01:15,251
how much I liked the older woman.

1346
01:01:15,452 --> 01:01:18,421
I felt like that way,
she wouldn't leave me.

1347
01:01:19,189 --> 01:01:21,123
But then they later said,

1348
01:01:21,492 --> 01:01:22,893
"Okay! I got it."

1349
01:01:22,894 --> 01:01:24,960
You should know the line.

1350
01:01:24,961 --> 01:01:27,564
I think he's coming on too strong now.

1351
01:01:27,565 --> 01:01:30,200
I feel like, as a younger man,

1352
01:01:30,201 --> 01:01:32,335
he can't keep his feelings to himself.

1353
01:01:32,903 --> 01:01:34,670
So, if you could go on a date
with someone else,

1354
01:01:34,671 --> 01:01:37,640
Jun Han would be your second choice,
right?

1355
01:01:40,477 --> 01:01:41,377
I think so.

1356
01:01:44,381 --> 01:01:46,115
Got it. Okay.

1357
01:01:48,051 --> 01:01:55,391
(One is more invested emotionally
than the other. What will happen to them?)

1358
01:01:56,627 --> 01:01:58,061
That's good.

1359
01:01:58,562 --> 01:02:01,197
Great work. Thanks for driving.

1360
01:02:01,198 --> 01:02:02,064
(Ji Hye and Jin Woo arrive.)

1361
01:02:03,066 --> 01:02:04,566
Were you tired on the way?

1362
01:02:05,536 --> 01:02:06,369
A little bit.

1363
01:02:08,172 --> 01:02:09,273
I'm kidding.

1364
01:02:09,274 --> 01:02:11,174
I had fun on the way.

1365
01:02:11,308 --> 01:02:12,608
(Staring)

1366
01:02:12,609 --> 01:02:14,644
- You had your hair down yesterday.
- Yes.

1367
01:02:18,682 --> 01:02:19,549
What?

1368
01:02:20,317 --> 01:02:22,585
You look pretty with your hair up.

1369
01:02:22,586 --> 01:02:23,753
(Smiling)

1370
01:02:23,754 --> 01:02:24,520
Oh, my.

1371
01:02:24,822 --> 01:02:26,724
I brought a hair tie.

1372
01:02:26,725 --> 01:02:27,524
Why?

1373
01:02:27,991 --> 01:02:29,024
To tie my hair?

1374
01:02:29,827 --> 01:02:30,927
I wouldn't tie it for you.

1375
01:02:31,829 --> 01:02:33,763
It's easier to eat with your hair tied up.

1376
01:02:34,064 --> 01:02:36,832
You're thoughtful enough
to bring a hair tie.

1377
01:02:38,035 --> 01:02:39,502
Jin Woo is handsome.

1378
01:02:39,670 --> 01:02:41,771
(Giggling)

1379
01:02:41,872 --> 01:02:43,806
You give off player vibes.

1380
01:02:43,807 --> 01:02:46,409
Player? That's not a good word.

1381
01:02:46,410 --> 01:02:48,044
It is. Why not?

1382
01:02:48,045 --> 01:02:49,579
You could say "a romantic" instead.

1383
01:02:50,214 --> 01:02:52,081
"Player" doesn't sound good.

1384
01:02:53,650 --> 01:02:56,085
Right. You seem like a romantic.

1385
01:02:56,353 --> 01:02:57,553
Let me give it to you.

1386
01:03:00,190 --> 01:03:02,124
Okay. I'll tie my hair with this tomorrow.

1387
01:03:04,895 --> 01:03:06,162
(Satisfied)

1388
01:03:06,163 --> 01:03:07,163
I like that.

1389
01:03:07,664 --> 01:03:09,598
You must be so nice to your girlfriend.

1390
01:03:14,838 --> 01:03:17,073
- That looks good. Drink that too.
- Okay.

1391
01:03:18,242 --> 01:03:19,342
Isn't it hot?

1392
01:03:19,343 --> 01:03:21,010
(Taking a bite)

1393
01:03:21,144 --> 01:03:22,678
(Flicking)

1394
01:03:23,381 --> 01:03:25,148
That was so sweet.

1395
01:03:28,518 --> 01:03:30,252
(Younger Man Jin Woo flirts nonstop.)

1396
01:03:30,253 --> 01:03:32,187
- Right.
- That looked so natural.

1397
01:03:33,223 --> 01:03:34,924
Small gestures like that...

1398
01:03:35,225 --> 01:03:36,926
- give older women butterflies.
- I'm an alpha male.

1399
01:03:37,895 --> 01:03:39,796
Please stop saying that.

1400
01:03:41,832 --> 01:03:42,932
Did you say you were a good cook?

1401
01:03:43,600 --> 01:03:44,700
I've been living alone for a while.

1402
01:03:45,068 --> 01:03:46,668
Can you make me kimchi stir-fried pork?

1403
01:03:47,438 --> 01:03:50,306
Spicy stir-fried pork is my comfort food.

1404
01:03:50,574 --> 01:03:51,340
Then...

1405
01:03:51,809 --> 01:03:54,109
should I make it for dinner today?

1406
01:03:55,112 --> 01:03:55,978
Okay.

1407
01:03:56,313 --> 01:03:57,713
(Nodding)

1408
01:03:58,682 --> 01:04:01,784
There's a movie I really liked.

1409
01:04:01,853 --> 01:04:03,219
"Us and Them."

1410
01:04:03,654 --> 01:04:05,288
I saw that.

1411
01:04:06,156 --> 01:04:06,956
A Taiwanese movie.

1412
01:04:09,026 --> 01:04:10,193
(High-five)

1413
01:04:12,062 --> 01:04:13,229
He looks like he's glitching.

1414
01:04:13,430 --> 01:04:14,296
I saw that three times.

1415
01:04:15,999 --> 01:04:17,333
The main actress also filmed...

1416
01:04:17,634 --> 01:04:18,801
"Better Days."

1417
01:04:18,802 --> 01:04:20,169
I saw that one.

1418
01:04:20,370 --> 01:04:21,721
You know good movies.

1419
01:04:21,746 --> 01:04:22,838
(They have similar tastes in movies.)

1420
01:04:23,340 --> 01:04:25,308
I saw that twice too.

1421
01:04:26,777 --> 01:04:27,643
We're meant to be.

1422
01:04:30,213 --> 01:04:31,146
That's good.

1423
01:04:32,382 --> 01:04:35,017
When you mention a movie
and the other person says they love it,

1424
01:04:35,018 --> 01:04:36,652
it makes me feel like...

1425
01:04:37,087 --> 01:04:37,920
You feel connected?

1426
01:04:38,089 --> 01:04:40,422
When they say they loved it too,
I go crazy.

1427
01:04:41,291 --> 01:04:42,725
What's the latest drama you watched?

1428
01:04:43,160 --> 01:04:44,127
- Drama?
- Yes.

1429
01:04:44,928 --> 01:04:45,928
"When Life Gives You Tangerines."

1430
01:04:46,630 --> 01:04:48,197
I had to stop watching in the middle...

1431
01:04:48,198 --> 01:04:49,098
because I was crying too much.

1432
01:04:49,099 --> 01:04:50,333
I cried during every episode.

1433
01:04:50,334 --> 01:04:52,735
- Every episode made me cry.
- I cried every time.

1434
01:04:53,070 --> 01:04:55,338
Not just when watching something,

1435
01:04:56,573 --> 01:04:58,274
but do you cry often in everyday life?

1436
01:04:59,309 --> 01:05:00,175
No.

1437
01:05:00,610 --> 01:05:01,643
Maybe twice a year?

1438
01:05:02,245 --> 01:05:04,012
- Really?
- Once or twice?

1439
01:05:07,418 --> 01:05:08,250
Do you cry often?

1440
01:05:09,753 --> 01:05:10,954
(Nodding)

1441
01:05:10,955 --> 01:05:12,088
Really?

1442
01:05:13,623 --> 01:05:14,923
I'll give you tissues every time.

1443
01:05:15,659 --> 01:05:16,935
What do you think of a guy
who cries a lot?

1444
01:05:17,761 --> 01:05:19,695
I guess it's cute.

1445
01:05:21,398 --> 01:05:23,466
I should find it cute. I can't hit him...

1446
01:05:23,467 --> 01:05:25,267
to make him stop crying.

1447
01:05:26,503 --> 01:05:28,437
Do you cry when you're really touched?

1448
01:05:29,740 --> 01:05:31,841
I'm really empathetic.

1449
01:05:31,842 --> 01:05:33,008
"What would I do if I were them?"

1450
01:05:33,443 --> 01:05:34,877
"What would I do in that situation?"

1451
01:05:35,212 --> 01:05:37,747
He's in touch with his emotions.

1452
01:05:39,392 --> 01:05:41,660
(Ji Hye is rational.)

1453
01:05:41,685 --> 01:05:42,919
You must be really empathetic.

1454
01:05:42,920 --> 01:05:43,953
(Jin Woo is more emotional.)

1455
01:05:44,821 --> 01:05:47,856
It's interesting how we're
on different emotional wavelengths.

1456
01:05:49,590 --> 01:05:50,693
Since we're this different...

1457
01:05:50,927 --> 01:05:52,761
It'll be fun
because you're different from me.

1458
01:05:54,398 --> 01:05:56,532
Do you like someone similar to you...

1459
01:05:56,533 --> 01:05:58,634
or different from you?

1460
01:05:58,969 --> 01:05:59,902
Different from me.

1461
01:06:00,904 --> 01:06:01,871
Do you remember...

1462
01:06:01,872 --> 01:06:03,672
I said I wanted to date
someone better than me?

1463
01:06:03,673 --> 01:06:04,406
Yes.

1464
01:06:05,342 --> 01:06:06,575
Yes. You said that.

1465
01:06:07,277 --> 01:06:09,745
You said you'd date someone
who shines and help them shine even more.

1466
01:06:09,913 --> 01:06:12,681
Yes, that's what I hope to do.
And likewise,

1467
01:06:13,950 --> 01:06:15,217
I could learn from her...

1468
01:06:15,218 --> 01:06:16,585
and become a better person too.

1469
01:06:16,586 --> 01:06:17,419
Right.

1470
01:06:18,923 --> 01:06:22,291
That's a mature relationship.

1471
01:06:23,560 --> 01:06:25,094
If you date someone too similar to you,

1472
01:06:25,095 --> 01:06:26,629
you don't really grow in the relationship.

1473
01:06:27,197 --> 01:06:29,966
I told you I don't have many hobbies.

1474
01:06:29,967 --> 01:06:32,301
So if I dated someone
who has a lot of hobbies,

1475
01:06:32,602 --> 01:06:35,404
he could be a good influence on me.

1476
01:06:36,173 --> 01:06:38,340
Because he's different from me.

1477
01:06:38,576 --> 01:06:39,842
He inspires you.

1478
01:06:39,843 --> 01:06:41,443
Yes. Seeing him...

1479
01:06:41,679 --> 01:06:43,712
makes me want to start a new hobby.

1480
01:06:43,947 --> 01:06:46,115
So now...

1481
01:06:47,017 --> 01:06:49,618
I'm more interested
in people different from me.

1482
01:06:49,643 --> 01:06:50,885
(Interested in someone different from her)

1483
01:06:51,389 --> 01:06:53,556
Because I want to change.

1484
01:06:54,724 --> 01:06:57,392
I've never dated someone older than me,

1485
01:06:57,393 --> 01:06:58,827
so I wonder if I did,

1486
01:06:59,529 --> 01:07:02,498
Would I be more loved and grow...

1487
01:07:02,499 --> 01:07:03,632
as a person?

1488
01:07:04,768 --> 01:07:05,668
Someone younger...

1489
01:07:05,669 --> 01:07:07,937
Dating someone older would be better...

1490
01:07:07,938 --> 01:07:09,271
than dating someone younger.

1491
01:07:11,908 --> 01:07:12,808
What do we do?

1492
01:07:13,176 --> 01:07:14,409
- What?
- I'm younger than you.

1493
01:07:15,145 --> 01:07:16,011
I'm younger than you.

1494
01:07:17,247 --> 01:07:18,380
Should we date?

1495
01:07:18,883 --> 01:07:20,483
Do you want to date me?

1496
01:07:22,486 --> 01:07:25,721
(He can't help smiling.)

1497
01:07:26,323 --> 01:07:27,824
- It's no joke.
- Those comments.

1498
01:07:27,825 --> 01:07:28,691
It's direct.

1499
01:07:28,692 --> 01:07:31,927
Jin Woo is unexpectedly bold.

1500
01:07:31,928 --> 01:07:34,530
- They have really good banter.
- They click very well.

1501
01:07:34,531 --> 01:07:35,564
They have similar tastes too.

1502
01:07:35,565 --> 01:07:38,267
Should we date? Do you want to date me?

1503
01:07:39,402 --> 01:07:41,470
(Grinning)

1504
01:07:43,306 --> 01:07:44,373
This is driving me crazy.

1505
01:07:45,610 --> 01:07:46,976
He's cute for sure.

1506
01:07:47,644 --> 01:07:50,012
He's funny and cool.

1507
01:07:51,148 --> 01:07:54,750
I just kept laughing
and lost track of time.

1508
01:07:54,751 --> 01:07:55,718
I had a lot of fun.

1509
01:07:57,020 --> 01:07:58,354
Did you send me the QR last night?

1510
01:08:01,124 --> 01:08:02,191
What made you think that?

1511
01:08:03,226 --> 01:08:06,795
I just felt like you sent that picture.

1512
01:08:06,931 --> 01:08:09,832
As soon as I opened it, I was sure.

1513
01:08:09,833 --> 01:08:11,767
"It must be Jin Woo."

1514
01:08:12,869 --> 01:08:13,769
"It's Jin Woo."

1515
01:08:13,870 --> 01:08:16,772
How could you tell
just from looking at the street?

1516
01:08:17,274 --> 01:08:19,608
It was from the angle you would get...

1517
01:08:19,609 --> 01:08:24,413
if you were standing
in the first guys' room.

1518
01:08:26,116 --> 01:08:29,785
(Jin Woo's Love QR from the first night)

1519
01:08:31,421 --> 01:08:32,421
"It's Jin Woo."

1520
01:08:32,422 --> 01:08:33,322
(Shy)

1521
01:08:33,323 --> 01:08:34,256
Am I right?

1522
01:08:35,825 --> 01:08:39,761
I came running to ask you out today.

1523
01:08:42,866 --> 01:08:45,067
Right? After seeing the QR code,

1524
01:08:45,268 --> 01:08:46,902
did you think...

1525
01:08:46,903 --> 01:08:49,538
I'd ask you out if I had a chance?

1526
01:08:50,173 --> 01:08:53,642
Well, I didn't know
the guys would be asked...

1527
01:08:53,877 --> 01:08:55,744
to ask the girls out.

1528
01:08:55,745 --> 01:08:57,479
If they hadn't done that...

1529
01:08:57,847 --> 01:08:59,609
and told the girls to ask the guys out,

1530
01:09:00,042 --> 01:09:02,554
if the other women allowed me,
I thought of asking you out.

1531
01:09:04,181 --> 01:09:05,647
- You wanted to ask me out?
- Yes.

1532
01:09:09,114 --> 01:09:11,047
I was really about to ask you on a date.

1533
01:09:12,047 --> 01:09:13,081
You sent me a Love QR.

1534
01:09:15,547 --> 01:09:17,514
So I thought we could talk.

1535
01:09:19,547 --> 01:09:21,247
I was going to take you out first.

1536
01:09:21,247 --> 01:09:22,481
"Come on."

1537
01:09:23,007 --> 01:09:24,007
"You want to go out?"

1538
01:09:25,414 --> 01:09:27,581
It's true. I mean it.

1539
01:09:28,314 --> 01:09:29,314
I love this.

1540
01:09:29,547 --> 01:09:32,114
Anyway, this is a first date
for both of us.

1541
01:09:32,114 --> 01:09:33,114
Yes.

1542
01:09:33,114 --> 01:09:35,381
- I'll probably remember this forever.
- Exactly.

1543
01:09:36,245 --> 01:09:38,712
- I was thinking the same thing.
- There's no way I'll forget this.

1544
01:09:40,145 --> 01:09:42,878
- This is becoming a great memory.
- Yes, you'll be reminded of it.

1545
01:09:42,945 --> 01:09:44,545
- It's something only we share.
- Yes.

1546
01:09:45,245 --> 01:09:46,245
You're right.

1547
01:09:47,278 --> 01:09:49,545
It's been a while
since I've talked to someone...

1548
01:09:49,545 --> 01:09:51,145
who felt like a friend and a partner.

1549
01:09:51,412 --> 01:09:53,478
So it was really fun to go on a date.

1550
01:09:54,178 --> 01:09:57,212
I was as excited
as much as I felt comfortable.

1551
01:09:57,212 --> 01:09:58,978
And I kept thinking...

1552
01:09:59,545 --> 01:10:02,178
that I could like her more.

1553
01:10:06,612 --> 01:10:08,578
Last night,
when answering the question card,

1554
01:10:08,745 --> 01:10:12,145
Ji Hye chose a partner
who gives a dopamine rush.

1555
01:10:12,145 --> 01:10:13,378
- That's right.
- Yes.

1556
01:10:13,378 --> 01:10:17,245
Do you think she felt dopamine
from Jin Woo?

1557
01:10:17,545 --> 01:10:20,712
But considering this is their first date,

1558
01:10:21,078 --> 01:10:24,012
I'd say he gave her
a nice little dopamine boost.

1559
01:10:24,678 --> 01:10:27,345
- A little dopamine boost.
- So he made an impression?

1560
01:10:28,145 --> 01:10:31,445
Jin Woo is really good with people.

1561
01:10:31,578 --> 01:10:34,278
- So he gave a little boost at least.
- Really?

1562
01:10:35,078 --> 01:10:40,012
In a way, it feels like Ji Hye is
also falling for...

1563
01:10:40,412 --> 01:10:42,112
Jin Woo's gentle charm.

1564
01:10:42,345 --> 01:10:45,478
I think I saw a different side of him.

1565
01:10:45,478 --> 01:10:48,345
He seems more comfortable
when he's alone with an older woman,

1566
01:10:48,345 --> 01:10:50,312
and the talk comes more naturally.

1567
01:10:50,378 --> 01:10:53,445
I'm sure he could be like that
with the other women too.

1568
01:10:54,278 --> 01:10:57,678
- So he might make a move for them.
- Like asking them out?

1569
01:10:58,045 --> 01:11:01,345
(Then a message arrives.)

1570
01:11:01,512 --> 01:11:02,978
(What message did
all the couples receive?)

1571
01:11:02,978 --> 01:11:04,045
We got a text.

1572
01:11:04,978 --> 01:11:05,978
Suddenly?

1573
01:11:08,012 --> 01:11:11,278
(The women and the men got flustered
by the sudden message.)

1574
01:11:12,145 --> 01:11:14,345
Are they telling us to end our date?

1575
01:11:14,345 --> 01:11:15,412
I don't want to.

1576
01:11:30,788 --> 01:11:32,388
I'm going to Hongcheon.

1577
01:11:32,388 --> 01:11:33,522
Chuncheon for me.

1578
01:11:34,122 --> 01:11:35,922
- How do I get there?
- How can I get there?

1579
01:11:36,255 --> 01:11:37,888
It says I should go there alone.

1580
01:11:37,888 --> 01:11:38,922
Me too.

1581
01:11:39,122 --> 01:11:40,009
I have to go somewhere else.

1582
01:11:40,034 --> 01:11:41,255
(They must move to separate locations.)

1583
01:11:41,331 --> 01:11:42,831
(Women and men are separated
to different places.)

1584
01:11:43,091 --> 01:11:44,091
What?

1585
01:11:44,091 --> 01:11:45,324
- Why?
- They are split up.

1586
01:11:46,257 --> 01:11:47,324
I need to go to this place.

1587
01:11:48,657 --> 01:11:50,524
- It's time to go now.
- Yes.

1588
01:11:50,524 --> 01:11:52,791
- How was the date?
- It was so much fun.

1589
01:11:52,791 --> 01:11:54,324
I even lost track of time.

1590
01:11:54,924 --> 01:11:57,457
If I ask you out again next time,

1591
01:11:58,724 --> 01:11:59,924
would you like it?

1592
01:12:00,291 --> 01:12:01,291
Yes.

1593
01:12:01,291 --> 01:12:03,191
It would be weird not to.

1594
01:12:03,191 --> 01:12:05,191
Right. What if you get the chance?

1595
01:12:05,624 --> 01:12:06,757
- If I get the chance?
- Yes.

1596
01:12:06,757 --> 01:12:07,757
I should ask you out.

1597
01:12:09,183 --> 01:12:10,183
You don't sound enthusiastic.

1598
01:12:11,557 --> 01:12:13,791
- There was no enthusiasm.
- I should, and I will.

1599
01:12:14,991 --> 01:12:16,757
I told you earlier.

1600
01:12:17,424 --> 01:12:20,391
But it's your choice,
so it doesn't have to be me.

1601
01:12:23,391 --> 01:12:25,157
If we both get zero votes after this,

1602
01:12:25,591 --> 01:12:27,191
- Then...
- we'd betray each other.

1603
01:12:27,191 --> 01:12:28,991
- we might end up fighting.
- We'd turn on each other.

1604
01:12:30,591 --> 01:12:33,524
(Where will everyone's hearts lead them
after the date today?)

1605
01:12:34,357 --> 01:12:36,691
(The younger men head
to the next location.)

1606
01:12:36,691 --> 01:12:38,157
Where are they going?

1607
01:12:39,524 --> 01:12:43,124
(They gather at a mysterious place.)

1608
01:12:44,491 --> 01:12:46,491
(Meanwhile,)

1609
01:12:46,491 --> 01:12:49,791
(the older women also arrive
at a new location.)

1610
01:12:49,991 --> 01:12:52,391
- Why did they bring us together?
- I know.

1611
01:12:52,457 --> 01:12:54,191
- I'm scared.
- So curious.

1612
01:12:55,224 --> 01:12:56,424
There must be a reason.

1613
01:12:57,557 --> 01:13:00,524
- We must be going on a blind date.
- I know, right?

1614
01:13:00,524 --> 01:13:01,757
(Why did they gather separately?)

1615
01:13:01,791 --> 01:13:04,591
Seeing how they split the guys
and ladies up,

1616
01:13:05,057 --> 01:13:07,424
- another man or woman might...
- Join them?

1617
01:13:07,424 --> 01:13:10,157
That's what I expect,
but isn't it too fast?

1618
01:13:24,091 --> 01:13:29,357
Many older women say
that I'm not really a younger man.

1619
01:13:33,491 --> 01:13:37,424
Since I'm a man with passion,
I just want to give love.

1620
01:13:40,124 --> 01:13:43,824
Hang on, ladies. I'll be right there.

1621
01:13:45,357 --> 01:13:48,157
- Gosh!
- Seriously, a new guy?

1622
01:13:48,157 --> 01:13:50,857
- A new guy on the second day!
- Isn't he joining them too soon?

1623
01:13:52,024 --> 01:13:54,424
(Meanwhile,)

1624
01:13:55,757 --> 01:13:57,424
(a car heads toward the younger men.)

1625
01:14:03,291 --> 01:14:06,757
- You've got to be kidding me.
- I mean, look at her car!

1626
01:14:06,757 --> 01:14:08,924
(A new woman arrives in a striking car.)

1627
01:14:10,591 --> 01:14:14,324
I'd say I'm pretty well-rounded.

1628
01:14:15,657 --> 01:14:19,557
My intelligence, personality,
and looks are all flawless.

1629
01:14:20,857 --> 01:14:22,257
(A commanding presence)

1630
01:14:22,257 --> 01:14:23,591
She said that herself?

1631
01:14:24,857 --> 01:14:28,891
I've already bought a house
in a prime location in Korea.

1632
01:14:28,891 --> 01:14:30,891
This is insane. She's an all-rounder.

1633
01:14:31,657 --> 01:14:33,757
I'm confident.

1634
01:14:33,757 --> 01:14:35,724
They'll like me in the end.

1635
01:14:36,157 --> 01:14:37,557
This is no joke!

1636
01:14:37,557 --> 01:14:38,557
Ladies,

1637
01:14:39,324 --> 01:14:40,624
sorry for the intrusion.

1638
01:14:42,991 --> 01:14:46,524
Hello.

1639
01:14:46,524 --> 01:14:49,591
They saw her!

1640
01:14:49,591 --> 01:14:53,457
(Their eyes dart around
as the new older woman arrives.)

1641
01:14:57,857 --> 01:14:59,191
Jin Woo, stay strong!

1642
01:14:59,657 --> 01:15:01,624
Don't fall for her, Jin Woo.

1643
01:15:01,624 --> 01:15:02,857
You promised me.

1644
01:15:02,857 --> 01:15:03,924
(I'm watching you, Jin Woo.)

1645
01:15:03,924 --> 01:15:06,357
(The younger men go on a date
with a new older woman.)

1646
01:15:06,724 --> 01:15:07,991
What's your type?

1647
01:15:08,357 --> 01:15:11,791
I like someone kind-hearted
over someone good-looking.

1648
01:15:12,357 --> 01:15:13,724
Would you like some bread?

1649
01:15:13,724 --> 01:15:15,191
Would you like a fork?

1650
01:15:15,657 --> 01:15:16,857
Shall I cut it for you?

1651
01:15:17,524 --> 01:15:18,691
I can get you a blanket.

1652
01:15:19,391 --> 01:15:20,524
Thank you.

1653
01:15:20,524 --> 01:15:21,824
(The younger men make their moves.)

1654
01:15:22,157 --> 01:15:23,691
I think I'm figuring out your type.

1655
01:15:23,691 --> 01:15:25,291
(The new younger man's first date
with the older women)

1656
01:15:25,957 --> 01:15:26,957
He's cool.

1657
01:15:27,857 --> 01:15:29,024
I got excited a little.

1658
01:15:30,357 --> 01:15:33,791
I've only dated women older than me.

1659
01:15:34,057 --> 01:15:36,257
Yes, age doesn't really matter.

1660
01:15:36,424 --> 01:15:38,724
That's not what you said earlier.

1661
01:15:39,124 --> 01:15:42,557
No, I meant...

1662
01:15:42,724 --> 01:15:44,791
- You know what I mean, right?
- I don't.

1663
01:15:45,924 --> 01:15:48,157
(A new younger man appears
to fluster the older women?)

1664
01:15:49,224 --> 01:15:50,957
Hello.

1665
01:15:50,957 --> 01:15:54,057
(Are they finally meeting
a welcome newcomer or a new rival?)

1666
01:15:54,324 --> 01:15:56,191
She looks really young.

1667
01:15:57,057 --> 01:15:59,191
I think she's pretty and charming.

1668
01:15:59,724 --> 01:16:00,924
(Surprised)

1669
01:16:00,924 --> 01:16:02,057
He's handsome.

1670
01:16:02,457 --> 01:16:04,691
I can see why he's the game changer.

1671
01:16:05,657 --> 01:16:08,091
- Hello, nice to meet you.
- Hello.

1672
01:16:08,557 --> 01:16:10,224
He put me on edge.

1673
01:16:11,257 --> 01:16:13,257
I got nervous, to be honest.

1674
01:16:15,357 --> 01:16:16,442
I got a message.

1675
01:16:16,467 --> 01:16:18,657
(Surprised)

1676
01:16:18,657 --> 01:16:19,957
A job box?

1677
01:16:19,957 --> 01:16:21,357
(It's time to reveal their jobs.)

1678
01:16:21,357 --> 01:16:22,691
A box has arrived.

1679
01:16:23,357 --> 01:16:25,991
Are they revealing their jobs already?

1680
01:16:25,991 --> 01:16:27,591
(They open each job box one by one.)

1681
01:16:27,591 --> 01:16:28,924
This one is mine.

1682
01:16:29,791 --> 01:16:31,057
I was so shocked.

1683
01:16:31,791 --> 01:16:33,324
Hold on.

1684
01:16:33,324 --> 01:16:34,424
I'm...

1685
01:16:34,924 --> 01:16:36,224
Are you serious?

1686
01:16:37,191 --> 01:16:39,757
It was cool and unexpected.

1687
01:16:40,491 --> 01:16:41,824
I'm now...

1688
01:16:41,824 --> 01:16:43,124
Really?

1689
01:16:43,291 --> 01:16:44,824
I never would have guessed.

1690
01:16:45,891 --> 01:16:48,424
(All shocked
at each other's unexpected jobs)

1691
01:16:48,924 --> 01:16:51,091
(What changes await the Yeon House?)

1692
01:16:51,091 --> 01:16:52,191
Dramaday.me
